title: susan's chicken divine
directions: Skin and debone chicken.
Combine rice, cream of chicken and mushroom soups. Add the extra mushrooms. Place in baking dish. Arrange broccoli over rice mixture.
Pour diluted cheese soup over broccoli.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then mix the next 5 ingredients together.
Put both mixtures together; mix well.
Add bacon bits just before serving.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic until tender. Add 3 cups chicken
broth,
milk,
mushroom
soup, tomato sauce and cream cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Stir as needed.	Add chicken. Heat
to boiling again.
Add spaghetti and cook over low heat until spaghetti is tender.
More milk or broth may be added if needed. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar again.

title: peanut butter dipped cocoa bonbons
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk in bowl.
Blend in powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until firm enough to handle (about 1 hour).
Shape into 1/2-inch balls and place on waxed paper.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight (uncovered). Centers should feel dry to touch.
Stir chips and shortening over hot, not boiling, water until melted.
Using a fork, dip each center into the peanut butter mixture.
Tap fork on side of pan to remove excess mixture.
Slide bonbons upside-down on the waxed paper.
Chill and store in a cool place.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen bonbons.

title: apricot delight
directions: Steam dried apricots in water.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, with a wooden spoon until the mixture falls away from sides of saucepan (234° to 238°).
Remove from heat; beat in the butter and allow to dry overnight.
Next day, shape into small balls and roll in coconut. Yields 50.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift
flour,
soda,
baking
powder
and sugar.
Cut in shortening and add buttermilk.
Roll out to desired thickness. Cut out biscuits.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for
to
12 minutes or until brown.
(Biscuits may be dipped in melted butter before placing on baking sheet.)

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Place eggs, oil and milk in another bowl and beat.
Then add dry ingredients; fold in the cut rhubarb.
Turn into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spoon topping all over batter.
Bake at 350°.

title: japanese salad
directions: Shake all ingredients together and refrigerate or make just before serving.

title: margaret's marinated mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms 2 days in refrigerator. Stir occasionally. Great snack!

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat 20 strokes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Pat into 1 large or 2 small greased pan with floured fingers.

title: t.j.'s finger cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Bring to a simmer, not stirring too much--till light brown at the edges.
Add vanilla at the end. Prepare pan while this is cooking.
Use cookie sheet with a lip--cover with aluminum foil.
Coat with butter.
Cover bottom of pan with saltine crackers.
Pour sugar/butter mixture evenly over layer of crackers and spread to cover.
Bake 5 minutes at 350 degrees.
Top with chocolate chips after crackers come out of the oven.
Chips will melt and you can spread them with a brush.
Top with your choice of nuts.
Press nuts down.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw veggies and drain.
Mix with soup, 1/2 c. cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can fried onions. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake another 5 minutes. Can be microwaved on high 4 minutes, turn and microwave another 4 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and microwave on high 1 minute.

title: cody's doggie biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead.
Roll on floured surface and cut into desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend Eagle brand condensed milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add vanilla pudding and mix.
Add milk and then add 1/2 to 3/4 container of Cool Whip, keep remaining Cool Whip for top of pudding.
The mixture will become thick.
Slice bananas.
Layer vanilla wafer cookies, bananas and pudding until gone.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle some crushed vanilla wafers on top for garnish.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream and spread over beans.
Sprinkle lemon juice over avocados. Layer over mayonnaise mixture.
Cover with picante sauce.
Sprinkle with cheeses, then onions.
Top with olives.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: light honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, mustard and mustard seed until smooth.
Serve over salad greens, onion rings or chicken fillets.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Stir together bananas, sugar, milk, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in Bisquick and chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place top side up on wire rack.
Cool completely, about 2 hours, before slicing.
Wrap tightly and store at room temperature up to 4 days or refrigerate up to 10 days.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and make into balls.
Roll each ball heavy in powdered sugar.
Place pecan half on top or inside each cookie.
Grease cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: chippers
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour to form stiff dough.
Stir in chips and pecans. Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add other juices. Add fruits.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw slightly and break into pieces.
Add Sprite.
Stir. Will serve 12 large servings or 24 small servings.

title: karen's fruit slush
directions: Mix sugar and boiling water.
Stir in orange juice and cans of water.
Add fruits.
Mix well.
Pour into individual serving glasses.
Freeze.
Enjoy!

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers in a square pan.
Add layer of pie filling and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat, then store in refrigerator and enjoy.

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: In large saucepot or Dutch oven, combine chicken or rabbit, beef short ribs, smoked ham, beef broth, tomatoes, bourbon, potato, chopped or dried parsley and thyme, salt, black and cayenne peppers.
Bring to a boil, uncovered.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add frozen lima beans, whole okra and corn. Cover saucepot and simmer 1/2 hour more until meat is tender.

title: cabbage and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saute pan.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: casada cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on box and let cool.

title: hot or cold chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breast in 3 cups water to which you have added 2 bouillon cubes (or use 3 cups stock).
When chicken is cool, cut off meat and cut into chunks. Melt butter.
Add pepper, then add flour.
Stir well with whisk.
Add 2 cups of the stock and the onion.
Stir until thick.
Add chicken meat and assorted cooked vegetables to sauce.
Mixture will be thick.
Make pie crust.
Add mixture.
Cover with top crust.
Coat with milk to make it brown. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be eaten hot or cold. Great for lunch box!

title: pork chops and stuffing bake
directions: Prepare package stuffing. Spoon stuffing across center of 3-quart shallow baking dish.

title: aunt evie's carrot cake
directions: On wax paper sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
On another piece of wax paper mix together the raisins and walnuts.
Use 2 tablespoons of the sifted flour mixture and toss with raisins and walnuts.
In large mixing bowl, beat together the sugar, oil and vanilla.
Thoroughly beat the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients in several additions, alternately with carrots and blend batter just until smooth after each addition.
Pour into angel cake pan (10 x 13 inches).
Batter will not come high in the pan after baking. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until tops springs back when lightly touched with finger, about 1 1/4
hours.
Place on wire rack to cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack, turn right side up.
Cool and spread top with cream cheese frosting.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto batter; cut through batter with knife several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream the butter, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs, vanilla and Ricotta.
Mix well.
Add baking soda, baking powder and flour. Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch and drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, soup, 1/2 of the cheese, almonds, onion and pepper.
Press lightly in a 2-quart casserole.
Add crushed crackers on top of casserole.
Squeeze butter generously over top of crackers.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine lard, salt and peanut butter; mix well. Add sugar, eggs and milk. Sift flour with soda and add to first mixture, blending well.
Drop from teaspoon on baking sheet greased with lard.
Press cookies lightly with a fork to flatten and to make ridged top.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Place peeled and sliced potatoes in the bottom of a greased casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours, stirring after 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and butter; add sugar and milk, one cup at a time. Then add flour and coconut.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Place all ingredients in a large baking dish and bake in a moderate oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir it once or twice, so that it does not burn on top.
Serve hot or cold (you can reheat it if you wish) with sour cream or heavy sweet cream.
It is enough for 8, if I am not one of them.

title: georgia's marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all vegetables and toss lightly.
Combine all other ingredients; stir well.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill for 12 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.

title: breath of spring delight
directions: To boiling water, add jello and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Cream the cheese.
Add vinegar, pineapple and nuts.
Fold into jello mixture.
Chill until congealed.
This salad will stand up well and has a bright spring color of green.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together and add to creamed mixture the flour, baking soda and salt.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls into small tins lined with 1-inch cupcake liners.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove and place 1 peanut butter cup in the center of each cookie.
Press gently into each cookie.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from tins.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Saute onion and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over hot dogs on buns.
Can be frozen for later serving.

title: creamy vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions; drain. Place in large bowl. Stir in soup and cream cheese. Transfer to 1-quart baking dish and top with seasoned croutons.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.	Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
Cook broccoli in bouillon water until tender.
Set aside.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended. Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly, for approximately 1 minute.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add broccoli and some of the water broccoli was cooked in.
Cook until blended.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes until light and fluffy.
Beat in 1/4 cup butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Put half in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle half of cornflakes on top, then marshmallows and some melted butter.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Crumble butter and top with pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese breakfast pizza
directions: Roll out pastry and fit into pizza pan.
Press up the sides and trim even with the top.
Bake on lowest rack of a 425° oven for 5 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Sprinkle bacon and cheese evenly over crust.
In a bowl, lightly beat eggs with sour cream and parsley until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Return to lowest rack and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned.

title: cheese pockets
directions: Mix together.
Place rounded teaspoonful of filling in center of dough squares.
Bring up corners and pinch together.
Boil pockets in large pan (salted water) for 10 minutes.
Carefully lift out individually with slotted spoon.

title: corn
directions: Cook on top of stove.

title: elsie's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 325°.
Cool.

title: crunchy slaw
directions: Slice onions thin and mix with both bags of slaw.
Place in refrigerator.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, oil, accent and seasoning packet from noodles.
Add oil and let set for a while. Toast almonds and sesame seeds.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad mix.
Crush noodles and mix into salad mix, add almonds and sesame seeds.
Serve.
Recipe works well halved!

title: easy chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Stir and heat sugar, butter and milk until it boils.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, stirring quickly until melted and blended.
Frost immediately as the frosting sets while cooling.

title: potato soup(original recipe)
directions: Put potatoes in large kettle; cover with water.
Add salt, onion and carrots.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and cheese.
Allow cheese to melt and serve. Do not drain off potato water.
Add milk to thin, if needed.

title: sweetheart pizza trio
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir together baking mix and yeast.
Add water and beat vigorously. Turn dough onto well floured board and knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Allow dough to rest a few minutes. Divide dough into 3 parts. Roll each part about 1/4-inch thick on ungreased baking sheet. Shape each into heart; pinch edge to make slight rim.
Spread tomato sauce almost to edge of each heart.
Layer with remaining ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 3 pizzas.

title: frozen chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Spread 3/4 of the crumbs on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and chocolate in medium pan.
Add the yolks and powdered sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, for a few minutes;
cool.
Fold in the beaten whites.
Pour over the crumbs.
Freeze.
Cover with the ice cream.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 of the crumbs. Freeze.
Serve in squares.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes (fine side of grater).
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste.
Add egg and stir.
Add enough flour to hold together.
Fry in Crisco or oil until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello, and stir until dissolved. Add cold water.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Chill until set.

title: sweet vidalia onion pie
directions: Put cracker crumbs in square casserole dish.
Pour butter over crackers.
Saute onions in margarine and when tender, place in casserole.
Mix 2 eggs and 1/3 cup of milk; pour over onions. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Heat oven to 325° with rack in lowest third, but not bottom position.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press crescent rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, creasing all seams.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place on top of crescent rolls. In separate bowl, whip eggs, adding milk as if you were scrambling the eggs.
Pour over top of sausage.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scandinavian rye bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup of the very warm water; stir in 1 teaspoon of the molasses.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Let stand, undisturbed, to proof until bubbly and double in volume, about 10 minutes.
Put rest of water and molasses with salt and shortening in a large bowl.
Stir in yeast mix, rye flour and caraway seed.
Add enough all-purpose flour to make a soft dough. Turn out and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Using flour to keep from sticking, place in greased bowl.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 2 loaves and place on cookie sheet 4 inches apart, which is greased and lightly sprinkled with cornmeal.
Let rise for 45 minutes or until double in bulk. Brush tops with water.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 35 minutes or until browned.
Remove from sheet and cool on rack.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-buttered pie dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Refrigerate overnight.
May also be used as a salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done.
While potatoes are cooking, brown beef in frying pan.
Add tomato soup, water and can of green beans (drained).
Let simmer.
Mash the potatoes and add egg and milk.
Put beef mixture on bottom of square pan.
Top, like dumplings, with the potato mixture and sprinkle the cheese on top of the potatoes.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted in a 350° oven.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Season breasts and bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cover each breast with a slice of cheese. Mix milk and soup and pour over chicken.
Cover top with cornbread Stove Top stuffing.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: mrs. butt's sugar cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine, sugars and oil; beat with mixer until very light.
Add eggs and vanilla; continue beating.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix until just combined.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy maple syrup
directions: Heat sugar in a saucepan.
Add the water and bring to a full boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the flavoring and butter.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken nut puffs
directions: Mix chicken and almonds and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup sifted flour all at once to broth mixture and cook over low heat until mixture leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating hard with a spoon after each addition until mixture is shiny.
Stir in chicken mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes until browned.
Serve hot or freeze.
To serve after freezing, thaw and heat at 250° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Tangy Sweet Sauce.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender in salt and water and drain.
Add soup, eggs, sugar, onions, cheese and 1/2 cup breadcrumbs.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Mix butter and other crumbs and put on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Place in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with chicken. Combine remaining ingredients except bread crumbs, stirring well. Spoon mixture over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add broth, water and Worcestershire.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions on box.
Make two layers.
Bake and let cool.
Split layers to make 4. I use sharp knife, that works fine.
Mix sour cream and sugar (reserve 3/4 cup for top and sides) and 1 package of coconut.
Spread this between layers.
Mix whipped topping together and frost top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle the other package of coconut on top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate. Best after 4 days.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion, zucchini, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain some of the juice and put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover with tomatoes; sprinkle on cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Stir onion in shortening until tender.
Cook rice separate. Also cook broccoli separate.
Add other ingredients to onion, broccoli and rice.
Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Add to mixture.
Put into casserole dish (sprayed) and top with cheese. Bake until cheese is melted and bubbly at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together milk and egg; add oil.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture. Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
May also use 1/4 cup sugar.

title: finger cookies
directions: Melt oleo; add other ingredients.

Mix well; shape in small (press hard) rolls or crescent shapes about diameter of finger. Melt a 12 ounce package of chocolate chips with a tablespoon of paraffin wax over hot water. Use 2 forks to dip rolls into chocolate mixture to coat and lay on waxed paper.
(Tastes like Butterfinger bars.)

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; stir in 1 cup flour, sugar and salt. Add egg and oil; stir until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour. Knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover with plastic wrap and towel.
Let rise until more than double (about 1 hour). Punch down.
Roll to fit 16-inch pizza pan.
Brush with oil.
Bake (without toppings) on lowest rack, at 450°, for 3 minutes.

title: yummy lemon cheese cake
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix; beat slowly with eggbeater or wire whip for 1 minute.
Do not overbeat!
Pour into baked and cooled graham cracker crust. Sprinkle graham crumbs over top to make it extra crunchy.
Chill and serve.
Takes only 15 minutes to make.

title: spicy chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken with onion, garlic cloves, salt and pepper.
Cube chicken and potatoes.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Use some of jalapeno juice to taste.
Spread on tostada or tortilla chips.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Whip egg.
Add Milnot, sugars, salt and vanilla.
Add enough snow to make good ice cream.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all well and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: leche flan(baked caramel custard)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Fill a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with water to a depth of 1/2-inch; place in oven.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is caramelized.
Pour quickly into an 8-inch square pan.
Tilt to coat bottom and sides evenly.
Cool slightly. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over caramel layer. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan of water in oven.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill. Loosen edges with knife and invert onto serving platter.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: ham broccoli ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli and onion. Snip parsley.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients and set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and combine with bread crumbs.
Add mustard, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and milk, blend well.
Add eggs and melted butter.
Place mixture in a well-greased loaf pan; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven
about 30 minutes.

title: short cut red beans and rice
directions: Drain 1 can beans.
Cut sausage into circles.
Fry; add onions, bell pepper and lower part of green onions and saute.
Add beans, tomato sauce, garlic and Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle with pepper.
Stir over medium heat to blend mixture.
Lower heat; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and onion top, and serve over rice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix oleo and chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding mixes with milk and spread over cream cheese.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: shake-a-pie-crust
directions: Combine all ingredients except water in Tupperware bowl with lid.
Shake until
mixed.
Add ice water, shake again and then roll.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with buttered cornbread with hot applesauce poured over the top.

title: dirty-bird cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl; do not beat.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cover with foil the last 20 minutes.
This is moist and keeps well.

title: yummy jumbo chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Place rolled oats in blender or food processor and process until finely ground.
Hint:

If you don't have a food processor or blender it's just as well to put your oats in a cup and use the flat end of one of your mixer tools to stir and crush the oats. Combine ground oats, flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
In another bowl, cream butter, sugars, vanilla and lemon juice together using an electric mixer.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir the flour mixture into egg mixture, blending well.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts to the dough and mix well. Using 1/4 cup of dough for each cookie, scoop round balls with an ice-cream scoop and place 2 1/2 inches apart on prepared baking sheet.
Bake until cookies are lightly browned, 16-18 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Store in a sealed container to keep them soft and chewy.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: split pea and barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 3 or 4-quart pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for about 1 hour until peas begin to fall apart when stirred and barley and vegetables are tender.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, salt and milk to a boil. Let boil for 1 minute, then add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Drop onto waxed paper.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water. Add other ingredients. Mix and roll out on floured surface. Cut with biscuit cutter or shape and put in muffin tins. NEEDS NO RISING TIME but you can allow them to rise for a little if you like. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Butter and ENJOY!

title: popcorn trash
directions: Have popped corn, cereals and pecans ready.
Mix remaining ingredients in heavy saucepan; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Put dry mix in large roaster pan.
Pour cooked mixture over dry mixture and stir good.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour or more; stir as needed.

title: ranch style bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Cut up potatoes into 2-inch squares and boil until soft, but not falling apart.
Combine meat, potatoes, soup and beans in a baking dish.
Top with cheese and cook in 350° oven until cheese melts and the dish is heated through.

title: old fashion grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish. Swirl to coat dish. Mix potatoes, sugar, milk, soda, flour and nutmeg. Mix in beaten eggs. Pour into hot dish. Bake at 350°. Check when crust begins to form around edges and on top. Stir under and let crust form again. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly coat a 9 x 13 baking pan with nonstick spray. In a bowl, combine chicken, cheese, 1/2 cup sour cream and chopped chiles. Spoon chicken evenly over tortillas and roll up. Arrange, seam side down, in pan. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Stir remaining cup of sour cream and taco sauce and spoon over enchiladas. Sprinkle with additional toppings, if desired.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to boil until oleo is melted.
Add salt and flour; beat until it forms a ball that leaves the sides of the pan; cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time; beat thoroughly after each addition.
Spread pastry onto ungreased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Remove; pierce bubbles with fork while hot.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese and mix together.
Put on top of cooled pastry.
Spread whipped topping over pudding mixture.
Melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons oleo over low heat.
Add confectioners sugar to make a thin glaze, adding 3 to 4 tablespoons milk.
Pour or drizzle chocolate glaze over whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or longer.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli, then cut up stick of oleo and cheese, adding to broccoli.
Place in greased baking dish.
Melt the 1/2 stick of oleo, mix with crushed crackers and place over top of broccoli.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken with potatoes
directions: Wash and cut chicken into serving pieces.
Arrange in a baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and arrange potatoes around chicken.
Sprinkle generously with oregano.
Dot potatoes and chicken with butter. Add water, salt and pepper to taste and top with lemon juice. Bake in medium oven at 350° to 375° for 50 minutes until chicken is done.
Baste occasionally with juice in pan.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mary spires' carrot cake
directions: Sift together first five ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well and then add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well. Add carrots, mix well.
Turn into three 8-inch layer cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
When completely cooled, fill and frost with Nut Frosting.

title: chicken filled ham rolls
directions: Divide chicken into 20 portions.
Roll into ham slices. Place, seam down, in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fry mushrooms until limp. Add flour and stir until bubbly.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt over medium heat and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and add sugar.
Mix good together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Then beat in the vanilla.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Add sugar to slightly beaten eggs.
Add pecans, then dry ingredients.
Bake in small muffin tins at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: Combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish; blend well.
Combine beef, egg, breadcrumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup soup mixture.
Shape into 6 patties; brown in skillet. Drain drippings from pan.
Combine remaining soup mixture, 1/2 cup water and a sprinkling of parsley; pour over patties.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
I turn them about 4 times.
Yields 6 servings.

title: super carrot raisin salad
directions: In a serving bowl, combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon into a smooth dressing.
Add carrots, raisins and pineapple to dressing and stir gently but thoroughly until salad is uniform.
Cover and chill for a minimum of 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving and drain liquid, if desired.
Use a slotted spoon to serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside. Saut celery and onion in butter in a large bowl; mix in chicken soup, sour cream and Parmesan cheese. Add spaghetti, diced chicken, salt and pepper. Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes (do not overcook).

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter.
Add corn and chilies.
Heat and serve.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and boiling water.
Cook until thick and then remove from heat.
Add jello; mix and cool.
Place strawberries, without juice, in baked pie shell.
Cover with cool mixture.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Poke holes in hot cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over hot cake. Warm caramel topping in microwave and pour over cake.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with Skor candy bars.

title: fudge
directions: Mix the sugar with the liquid. Add the chocolate chips and syrup. Boil gently to a "soft ball" stage.

Just before removing from the fire, add the butter. Cool, then beat the mixture until it thickens. Add the vanilla and salt. Pour into a buttered pan. Cut into squares. When cool, the fudge is ready for serving.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and place in an airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: chili with beans
directions: Soak
beans
overnight;
drain
water.
Pour
in tomato juice and
enough water to cover beans.
Simmer 1 hour.
Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Add meat, onions and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer until done.
Add water, if needed and adjust spices to taste.

title: cool rise sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add milk, sugar, salt, butter, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Add 3 cups flour; knead for 10 minutes.
Let sit for 20 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls about 1 teaspoonful. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and press 1 Hershey's Kiss in each.
Makes about 48.

title: nighty-nite cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar gradually.
Beat until glossy.
Add pecans and chocolate bits.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drop by teaspoon on foil lined cookie sheet.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven overnight.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza meatloaf
directions: Combine meat, cracker crumbs, 3/4 c. pizza sauce, onion, bell pepper, Parmesan cheese, mozzarella cheese, eggs and seasonings. Mix lightly.
Press meat mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Spread remaining pizza sauce over meat.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese begins to melt.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serves 8.

title: microwave goof proof fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in microwaveproof deep bowl except for margarine.
Lay stick of margarine on top of mixture.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until margarine melts.
Mix well.
If not thick, cook 1 minute at a time until thickened.
If desired, add 1/2 cup nuts.
Place in glass pie plate covered with margarine.
Pat out. Will harden in 5 minutes in freezer, 10 minutes in refrigerator or 20 minutes sitting on the countertop.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Crush garlic in salt.
Saute mushrooms with garlic, salt and olive oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Run all through food processor until smooth. Combine in large bowl or jar.
Refrigerate overnight to meld tastes.
Serve with croutons and sprinkling of extra chopped green onions, cucumbers, avocado, bell pepper and tomato. Makes 10 cups.

title: teriyaki pork chops
directions: Mix the brown sugar, soy sauce and dry mustard in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put pork chops on top and then put pineapple on top of pork chops.
(Do not use pineapple juice.)

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Mix in bowl first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil next 3 ingredients, then mix with dry ingredients with a whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in oblong pan until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with favorite icing while hot.

title: ann's hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Squeeze excess moisture, then wrap in a paper towel; refrigerate until dry.
Mix other ingredients. Add spinach.
Mix well.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tight and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight for up to 7 days. Slice and serve.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix gelatin, 3/4 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Beat milk and egg yolks together.
Add gelatin mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Lightly brown pork chops.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix soup, water, rice, 3/4 cup cheese, onion and mushrooms; pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(I usually just bake for 1 hour.)
Cover with remaining cheese, leave uncovered and place back in oven to melt cheese.

title: aunt rose's ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add molasses; beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart.
Put a drop of water on each one.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix above ingredients well and form into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: everybody's favorite chicken wings
directions: In saucepan, bring whiskey, soy sauce and sugar to a boil. Place chicken wings in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (larger if necessary).
Put wings in oven at 350°, long enough to warm.
Pour liquid over warmed wings and continue baking at 350° until liquid becomes sticky, about 1 to 2 hours. Great to make ahead and freeze.

title: rouse's chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat and onion in a small amount of grease.
Add tomatoes, bouillon cubes and 1 cup of water.
Simmer for 1 hour on medium heat.
Add garlic powder, mustard, oregano, cumin seed, chili powder and 1 cup of water.
Stir and simmer for 30 more minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour and cook until mixture thickens.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese and chopped onion. Also delicious over corn chips.

title: slippery dumplings
directions: Mix together flour and Crisco.
Add small amounts of water until dough is soft and workable.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Add to prepared chicken stock.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: In large skillet with lid, brown pork or chicken in a small amount of oil.
Add 1/2 cup of water; cover and simmer until tender (about 1 hour).
Drain pineapple chunks, saving the syrup. Combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Add the pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add this to the meat.
Cook and stir until the sauce thickens.
Add the pineapple chunks, pepper strips and onion.
Cover and cook 15 minutes (until the peppers and onions are soft).
Serve over rice.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix 1/2 box cake mix, butter, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs together.
Add other 1/2 box of cake mix, then stir.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop dough onto cookie sheet; bake until brown.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Makes enough to frost top and sides of layer cake.

title: leave it alone roast beef
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; pour into crock-pot.
Place roast into mixture.
Cook all day on low.
When tender, slice or shred.

title: lime jello salad
directions: In bowl combine Jell-O and water, mix until dissolved.
Add cream cheese, beat until dissolved; add ginger, juice and nuts. Pour into Jell-O mold, add pears and cherries.
Chill until set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix (knead) all ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil, then let cool.
Mix lemonade and pineapple juice with cooled mixture and cool.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 50.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix shortening with the sweet potatoes while they are warm and mash with a mixer.
Add the dry ingredients to the potatoes. Knead all of this together real good and make out into biscuits and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together into mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, food coloring, vanilla and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat well.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat again.
Mix vinegar and soda; add to cake mixture blending by hand.
Bake in loaf or layer at 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and garlic with salted water.
Strain vinegar mixture and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Garnish with sour cream and sprinkle with paprika.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer everything in bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and pumpkin.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix and add dry ingredients.
Last, add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cran-apple cobbler
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place first 3 ingredients in prepared dish and toss to mix well.
In bowl stir together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
With pastry blender or two knives cut in mayonnaise until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 or 4 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, poke tops with fork and drizzle mixture on top.

title: outstanding oats
directions: Soak oats and currants in distilled water overnight.
In the morning, pour off water from oats and add remaining ingredients. Stir and enjoy!

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well. Pour in greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes. Remove and ice while hot.

title: wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve hot.

title: refrigerator slaw dressing
directions: Heat all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Shape any flavor ice cream into balls.
Roll quickly in flaked coconut.
Put into freezer until very firm.
Serve with any flavor ice cream sauce.

title: never-fail chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; blend 1/2 minute on low speed. Beat 3 minutes on high speed; pour in 2 (9-inch) greased or 1 (9 x 12-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Easiest cake ever made.
Really never fail.

title: black pepper pickles
directions: Boil quart jars, lids and caps in hot water. Wash and scrub cucumbers in cool water (5 washings).
Small cucumbers work the best straight from the garden.

title: breakfast custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Pour into 6 to 8 custard
cups.
Place
on folded paper towel in frying pan with tight cover.
Pour cold water into pan half height of cups.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Allow to steam until set, about
15 minutes.
(Be
sure
water
doesn't
drip into custards when you remove the lid!).

title: pork and beans
directions: Look over and wash beans well.
Put water, beans, salt pork and salt into large pot.
Cook until tender.
Add molasses and tomato paste about 30 minutes before beans are done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
For topping, sprinkle crushed corn flakes with melted butter over casserole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Mix together and chill.
Right before serving, add slivered toasted almonds or serve with Chinese noodles on the side.

title: florida wedding punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat; stir until dissolved.
Cool and add chilled juices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour over decorated ice ring or ice cubes.
Makes 34 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: blue ribbon fried chicken
directions: Refrigerate overnight in dish the chicken, vinegar, salt and water to cover.
In bag, put flour, onion powder and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Dry in deep oil for 5 minutes, until lightly brown. Place lid loosely over pan to allow steam to escape.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and fry until golden brown.

title: canadian meat pie
directions: Put all ingredients except bread crumbs in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook slowly without cover for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons of the bread crumbs and let stand for 10 minutes.
If the fat is absorbed by the bread crumbs, no need to add more.
Cool and pour into pie crust; add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until the crust is golden.
Serve warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Mix well and chill.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: In heavy sauce pan or Dutch oven, brown meat and onions in oil over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients:
stir well.
Turn heat to low, cover and simmer soup for 2 to 3 hours.
Do not add any water!

title: sparkling punch
directions: Chill liquids. Mix and serve.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Beat sugar and butter together.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Add chocolate, applesauce and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Place flour in a bowl and add enough milk to make a dough consistency.
Knead on a floured board and roll to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 4 x 4-inch squares.

title: old fashioned sugar-free vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine NutraSweet, flour, salt and milk in large bowl. Microwave until mixture bubbles, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir about 1 cup hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Combine Cool Whip and vanilla. Add to chilled mixture. Freeze.
May be stored in individual servings in freezer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crused wafers and melted butter; press into bottom of rectangle dish.
Slice bananas lengthwise and cover bottom.
Avoid overly ripe bananas.
Use yellow skinned with green tip.
Mix together condensed milk and lemon joice; spread on top of bananas. Spread crushed pineapple on top of Eagle Brand layer.
Cover with whipped topping.
(8 to 9 ounces is plenty.)
Sprinkle coconut, chopped nuts and arrange cherries on top to designate serving size. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Easy, no cooking, pretty and good!!

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft) and shape into walnut size balls.
Place balls in a single layer on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until solid.
Store frozen meatballs until ready to cook.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Boil
water and sugar
to
dissolve
sugar.
Cool.
Add juices and bananas and put
in freezer.
Set out about 5 hours before serving and pour ginger ale over it in a punch bowl.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In oven
melt
butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix
Bisquick
and
fried chicken seasoning; coat chicken; place skin side down in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn over and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put nuts in pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Put aside.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Coat each with sugar mixture and drop on top of nuts in pan.
Melt butter and mix into remaining sugar mixture.
Scatter on top and even out.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn and cheddar cazuela
directions: Puree 4 cups corn in food processor.
Beat butter in mixer until fluffy.
Beat in cornmeal, sugar, cream cheese, and salt. Stir in corn puree and 1 cup whole corn.
Blend in cream.
Pour half of mixture in buttered ceramic baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of cheese and chopped chilies.
Pour in rest of mixture and cover with remaining cheese and chilies.
Cover with foil.
Bake one hour at 375°.
Cook 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: taco sauce(salsa)
directions: Use equal parts marshmallow cream and softened cream cheese. Good with apples and other fruits.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and cooked macaroni.
Put 1/2 of hamburger mixture in a baking dish, then add a layer of pepperoni and cover with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Watch carefully so cheese does not brown.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, add sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together, and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add flavorings.
Beat one minute longer.
Pour into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan and bake at 350°
about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan before removing.

title: mammaw's coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add a little milk.
Combine flour and sugar; add gradually to eggs.
Add remaining milk and coconut; cook until thick (medium heat on stove or microwave).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and margarine.

title: goober's radiator flush punch
directions: In a pitcher, combine all of the ingredients.
Serve over ice.
This is best when served with comic books.
Makes 5 cups.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda.
Stir into butter mixture with 1/2 cup lemonade concentrate.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Brush each cookie with lemonade and sprinkle with sugar after you remove from oven.

title: chocolate gravy mix
directions: In a medium sauce pan, mix all dry ingredients, blend with a spoon until mixed well. Before putting sauce pan on medium to low heat, add just enough milk that the cocoa mix is wet. Continue to stir until well blended, add milk as necessary, be careful that you don't add too much milk. Put on heat, add butter, keep a close eye on the gravy to make sure that it doesn't get too hot. It only needs to come to a low boil. After it reaches a low boil, cook about 2 to 3 minutes, stirring continuously. Serve with hot biscuits.

title: red sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Serve with appetizers.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Salt and pepper the slices.
Dip in egg and then in Italian bread crumbs. Fry in olive oil until golden brown; drain in paper towels.
Cover bottom of baking dish with the spaghetti sauce.
Place slices of eggplant in the dish; add sauce to cover.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350° (oven temperature).

title: stove top potpourri
directions: Place orange and apple peels on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° until dry, 4 to 5 hours.
Mix with crushed cinnamon sticks, whole nutmeg and a few whole cloves.
Place in airtight container.
To use, simmer small amount in water on the stove top.

title: johnie's southern fried chicken
directions: Add salt and pepper to corn meal.
Put chicken pieces into the meal in a brown paper bag and shake.
Heat Crisco in large iron skillet.
Arrange chicken pieces in the skillet.
Turn chicken once, then turn heat down to medium-low.
Let fry 45 minutes (no less) until golden brown and crispy.

title: dandy candies
directions: Mix all this until blended.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each part into a snake on waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Unwrap and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 2 dozen candies.

title: red "waldorf astoria" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans; set aside.
With a mixer, cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to sugar mixture.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Remove from mixer; sprinkle baking soda and vinegar over top of batter.
Fold very gently into batter until completely mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When cooled, frost with White Fluffy Frosting.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Simmer butter beans in water with bacon fat.
Saute carrot, onion and celery in margarine; add to beans.
Add tomatoes, garlic, salt and mustard.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix all together and form in small balls.
Chill, then dip in chocolate.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.

title: grandma's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine melted butter and brown sugar. Stir in 8-inch cake pan. On top of this, arrange pineapple slices.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Combine rice, sausage and remaining ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown.
Stir frequently and set aside.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook the rice and broccoli according to package directions. Saute the onion, celery and mushrooms in the butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramelized shallots and snow peas
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter with sugar over medium heat.
Add the shallots; stir gently to coat them with the syrup and cook until the syrup is browned and the shallots are tender, about 20 minutes.
Fill a large stock pot 1/2 full of water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Add the snow peas in batches, blanching them briefly until bright green in color, about one minute, then immediately remove with a slotted spoon.
Serve hot along side the caramelized shallots.

title: seasoned potato wedges
directions: Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise. Cut each half lengthwise into 3 wedges. Place in a single layer on a greased baking sheet. Spread mayonnaise over the cut sides of potatoes; sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender. Yield: 4 servings.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper. Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon together; pour in pan. Pour dry cake mix over mixture.
Pat nuts into mix evenly.
Spoon melted butter over nuts evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert onto tray and peel waxed paper off.

title: k cereal bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add cereal.
Bring sugar and syrup to a light boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well and pat down.
Melt small package of chocolate morsels and a small package of butterscotch morsels.
Spread over cereal mixture and let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: very good dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream and mix well. When it starts to thicken, add angel food cake.
Stir well until all pieces are covered.
Add the can of mandarin oranges and juice.
Mix and refrigerate.
Use 9 x 10-inch pan.

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Cool slightly. Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, cucumber and onion. Add a drop or two of green food coloring for more color. Place in covered dish. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook pasta in salted boiling water.
Gently drain and remove from water.
Don't overcook or they will split and fall apart. Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, parsley, sugar, egg, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Fill shells with this mixture.
Brown ground beef with remaining salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add garlic, spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour 1/2 sauce mixture in baking dish; top with filled shells.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven. Sprinkle with Parmesan about 5 minutes before done.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into round casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix pineapple, cream cheese, green pepper, onion and salt. Roll into a ball.
Chill.
Roll in nuts.
Chill again.
Can be spread on toasted buns or muffins as well as crackers.

title: one bowl pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl, mixing well. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add beaten eggs, corn syrup, oats and coconut; mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Add rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Pour 1 tablespoon melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, butter and milk, using double boiler, or microwave on Low.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Pour caramel, butter and milk mixture over baked cake.
Sprinkle chips and 1/2 cup nuts over caramel mixture.
Add the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle rest of nuts over all.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage as you would to smother and boil in salted water until tender, but still green.
Drain and reserve the liquid. Melt margarine in a deep skillet; fry ground meat with onion, garlic and seasoning until brown.
Mix cabbage with the meat, adding mushroom soup, green onion tops and boiled rice.
Pour into a greased flat Pyrex baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Before baking it too dry, add water from cabbage or more soup.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Mix together sour cream, cottage cheese, cream cheese, onions and pepper until well mixed. Brown hamburger, add tomato sauce to hamburger.
Put in large casserole one layer of noodles, a layer of cheese mixture, etc. until all noodles and cheese mixture are used.
Put the hamburger mixture on top of noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in bananas and marshmallows. Pour into 8-inch square baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine sugar and cornstarch and stir into undrained pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until thickened and smooth.
Cool.
Whip cream and fold into pineapple mixture.
Fold in half of cheese. Spread on chilled gelatin.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Chill overnight.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: In a
large mixing bowl, place cabbage, apples and celery; sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: 15 minute fettuccine alfredo
directions: In a large saucepan, stir cheeses, margarine and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add fettuccine.
Toss and serve.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Put crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and butter and 1 spoon vanilla for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust.
Cover with banana slices.
Put pineapples over crust first and bananas and whipped cream.
Decorate with nuts and cherry and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix the next 5 ingredients.
Add broccoli and place in a casserole dish that has been lightly greased with oleo.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: royal icing
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl at medium speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; mix well.
Beat 5 to 7 minutes.
May be tinted with paste food color.
Makes enough icing for 5 dozen cookies.

title: curly chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put uncooked spirals in the bottom of a large covered casserole dish.
Add 2 cups of water.
Put chicken on top.
Cover with half the sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover and add more sauce to spirals if necessary.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into small baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Break bread up.
Add water, salt, sugar and cocoa to broken bread.
Beat egg.
Add beaten egg and milk to bread mixture, then add melted butter and vanilla extract.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes or until center is set, not milky.
It seems to take longer, perhaps 45 minutes.
Spread with Hard Sauce.

title: italian cream pudding
directions: Cook 7 cups milk, vanilla pudding, vanilla and whiskey.
Pour over ladyfinger cookies.
Line up cookies and put in layers.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Add about 3/4 of the graham cracker crumbs into mixture.
Add
the egg whites last.
Cover bottom of pie pan
with rest
of
the
crumbs.
Pour
in
pudding	mixture. Refrigerate overnight and serve with whipped cream.

title: candy stick sweet pickles
directions: Slice pickles in half lengthwise; remove seeds and cut pickles into strips.
Put cut pickles into a large container and pour boiling water over them.
Let sit all day or overnight.
Place pickles in jars.
Bring mixture of other ingredients to a boil and pour over jarred pickles and seal.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add grated or diced cheese; stir until mixed, then add Worcestershire, oregano, garlic salt and pepper. Spread on Pepperidge Farm party rye (takes about 1 1/2 loaves). Place on a cookie sheet.
Freeze, then store in plastic bag in freezer.
To serve, place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour 1/4 cup cooking oil in large iron skillet and place in oven to heat.
Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add milk and egg and stir.
Pour in hot oil and stir quickly.
Add chilies, corn and cheese and mix well.
Pour into hot skillet and bake 20 minutes.

title: aloha crisps
directions: Preheat broiler.
Wrap one strip bacon around each pineapple chunk; secure with toothpick.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.
Makes about 16 crisps.

title: crisp vegetable aspic with horseradish dressing
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup tomato juice; set aside.
Combine 2 cups tomato juice, green onions, 1/4 cup green pepper, brown sugar, bay leaves, cloves and cinnamon in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Strain mixture, reserving juice.
Add gelatin mixture to hot tomato juice, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add remaining 1 cup tomato juice, lemon juice and hot sauce; stir well.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with seasonings and vinegar.
Add onion and sweet pickles.
Add mayonnaise; toss to mix.
Fold in eggs.
Chill well.

title: golden mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in salted water until tender. Drain. Place in mixing bowl. Add butter, sour cream, salt and pepper. Mix until well blended. Transfer to greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix into stiff dough.
Divide into 2 pieces and shape into rounds.
Prick the top with a fork and put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: bread pudding(spanish style)
directions: Bread can be substituted with old pieces of hardened Italian bread.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Place carrots, salt and water in a shallow pan with close-fitting cover and bake. Serve with butter and lemon juice. Chopped parsley may be added.

title: fig preserves
directions: Put figs, sugar
and
lemon
juice
in pot and bring to boil. Then slice the
lemon and put in and boil until bubbles come to top and burst.
Put in jars and seal.

title: ritz pie
directions: Set aside dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold dry ingredients into egg whites. Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg; mix well.
Add plain flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Make into ball and chill.
Roll out to fit 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place coconut in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 cake pan.
Add chopped nuts on top of coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour cake mix on top of nuts and coconut.
In another bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Drop this mixture by tablespoon on top of cake mix.
Use all the mixture, even though it looks like too much. Can add chopped nuts on top of cake before baking, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
In skillet saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In a small skillet, cook crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people or 11 people, if used on buffet.

title: mustard ring souffle
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler.
Mix sugar and gelatine. Stir in mustard, turmeric and salt.
Add water and vinegar to eggs, then stir in sugar mixture and cook over boiling water until slightly thickened, stirring all of the time.
Cool until thick. Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart mold (sprayed with Pam) and chill until firm.
Stuffed eggs around it and olives in center of mold makes a pretty appetizer or brunch tray.

title: roast with english yorkshire pudding
directions: Bake roast in glass pan with 1/2 inch fat drippings (ex.) Crisco or suet.
When done remove roast and set aside, keep warm. Mix flour, salt and evaporated milk diluted with the water.
Pour into pan drippings.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until raised and light brown.
Serve with roast.

title: elephant stew(children's recipe)
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fre, about 4 weeks at 465°. This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only in an emergency, as most people do not like hare in their stew.
This recipe has not been kitchen tested due to the scarcity of elephants.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in double boiler; cool.
Add whipped cream, pineapple, salt and vanilla.
Pour half of mixture into 8-inch square pan lined with crumbs.
Add another layer of crumbs and remaining mixture.
Top with crumbs.
Chill 24 hours.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together and cover with the salt.
Let set overnight.
Drain.
Add hot peppers, vinegar, spices (tied in a cloth bag) and sugar.
Allow to boil slowly until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add the horseradish at this time. Pack in pint jars.
Put on lids tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Mix bisquick, cracker crumbs, seasoned salt and pepper in one bowl.
Mix eggs and water in another bowl.
Drop pork chops into egg mixture then coat with bisquick mixture.
Spray a 12 inch non-stick skillet with cooking spray, heat over medium high heat. Cook pork in skillet 8-10 minutes, turning once until pork is slightly pink in the middle.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs lengthwise; remove yolks and set whites aside. In a small bowl, mash yolks with a fork. Add the cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Mix well. Stuff or pipe filling into egg whites. Garnish with paprika.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Using a shot glass, make "rounds" out of the Wonder bread.
Spread mixture fairly thick on bread.
Place on cookie sheet and broil.
May freeze ahead.

title: steak with mushrooms
directions: Place meat in freezer 1/2 hour before slicing.
Slice meat thin on the diagonal.
In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil. Add few pieces meat and brown well on all sides.
Set aside as it browns.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in a large saucepan with boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and layer in the bottom of a shallow 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: low-calorie crepes
directions: Place eggs in blender; whip to mix well.
Add salt, melted margarine, flour, baking powder and water.
Whip to blend thoroughly.
(Should batter become too thick, add a little extra water; stir to blend.) Cook in crepe pan according to manufacturer's directions.
Yield: 36 (6-inch, 15 cm) crepes.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until stiff while adding a little sugar at a time. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on foil covered cookie sheet. Place meringues in oven; turn oven off and leave overnight.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown beef, green pepper and onion in fat.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Combine salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar, vinegar and water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Cook on high until steaming freely and then simmer for 40 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shape sausage into 6 patties, brown and drain.
Add cabbage, cover and cook until cabbage begins to brown.
Add water and salt and cook done (about 10 minutes).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Spread in long casserole dish and top with crushed cheese crackers which have been mixed with margarine or top with cheese crackers, plain.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and shape into 2-inch balls.
Do not roll between hands too long, it will make them tough.
Place meatballs on ungreased flat pan or cookie sheet and place in oven for 20 minutes at 400° or until browned.
Remove from oven using slotted spoon.
Put into sauce and cook for 1 hour longer.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 425° for 8 minutes; remove from oven. Reduce heat to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into pieces.
In skillet, brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour and cheese pieces.
Turn into prepared shell.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining cheese slices; bake 3 minutes longer.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Slightly flatten each croissant. Dice the chicken. Add a little butter in skillet. Add onions and chicken and simmer. Put 1 1/2 tablespoons of chicken mixture in the center of each croissant. Roll in a ball or wrap like a turnover. Put croissant into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix cream of chicken soup, Velveeta and milk; melt together. Pour over croissants. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Microwave butter and peanut butter.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press in dish.
Combine morsels and shortening until melted.
Spread over.
Cover and chill.

title: peanut butter chocolate parfaits
directions: In a large heavy saucepan combine pudding mix and 3 1/2 cups milk (rather than amount listed in package directions).
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Lower the heat, then add green onions and mushrooms.
Slowly pour in beaten eggs while stirring the soup.
Remove from heat and serve immediately.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat and drain sweet potatoes.
Mash and add butter, beaten egg, warm milk, salt and brown sugar.
Whip with electric mixer until fluffy. Put in buttered casserole dish and top with marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortillas.
Arrange four dices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortillas.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, chip dip and dressing mix with beater until smooth.
Layer on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, dish or Tupperware.
Brown ground meat with onion.
Drain and cool slightly.
Layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Next, layer cheese, then lettuce, then tomatoes, pepper and olives. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add pecans, stirring gently until thoroughly coated.
Spread pecans in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain pecans on paper towels to absorb excess grease. Let cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 5 cups.

title: peach smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients. Cover and process until blended. Serve immediately in chilled glasses.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add sufficient milk to make a drop batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling liquid.
Cover closely and cook about 10 minutes.
The liquid must be kept boiling during the entire 10 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: bacon-cheese dogs
directions: Split hot dog; fill with cheese. Wrap with raw bacon, securing with toothpicks.
Put under broiler, cheese side down, until bacon is done. Turn hot dog and cook until bacon is done.

title: grung
directions: Mix both cheeses in 9-inch pie pan or glass pie plate.
Pour tomatoes over top of cheese evenly.
Beat egg in can of tomatoes to get remaining sauce out.
Pour egg over top of mixture in pan evenly.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Stir when removed.
Serve hot with Fritos or dipping chips/crackers.

title: traditional corn bread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute celery and onion until tender, about 3 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Pour over crackers in paper bag.
Shake.
Open bag; allow to dry for 1 hour.
May add little more garlic powder.

title: no bake cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Let sit at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add all other ingredients and beat about 20 minutes until slightly stiff. Pour into shell and refrigerate for about 4 to 6 hours.
Top with your favorite fruit filling (cherries, blueberries, apples, etc.).

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Coat with flour, salt and lemon pepper.
Brown meat in smoking hot oil.

title: pineapple inside cake
directions: Cream all together the sugar, butter and egg. Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture alternately with the drained pineapple juice.
Mix well (will be stiff). Fold in the pineapple.
Pour into a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: grossmommy's opera creams
directions: Mix
all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Let cook until
mixture
forms
a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
When pan is
almost
cold,
stir and stir and stir and stir.
It takes an
awful
lot
of stirring!
When you are finished stirring it,
mixture should be a light brownish-gray color.
Drop onto waxed paper; chill.

title: oyster perloo
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.	Remove bacon.
Saut onions, celery and pepper in bacon grease until onions are translucent.
Crumble bacon and return to pot.	Add drained oysters and cook until they release juice, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice; add water to reserved oyster juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Stir liquid into rice, bring to a boil, lower to a simmer, cover and cook exactly 20 minutes.
Remove pot from heat and let sit 20 minutes.
Fluff up rice with a fork. If needed add more seasonings, and serve.
Serves 4.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Steam or boil carrots until very soft. Drain well. Transfer to a large mixer bowl. While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Beat with mixer until smooth. Add flour and mix well. Add whipped eggs and beat well. Pour mixture into a 2 quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until light golden brown in color. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips or squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Grease large shallow baking dish.
Place 2 tablespoons water in bottom of dish.
Make layer of tortillas in dish, then layer of turkey, then layer of soup mixture.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used, ending with soup mixture. Top with cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours to blend flavors.
Bake, uncovered at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Mix 2 cups cookie crumbs with butter in bowl. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish. Layer ice cream, fudge topping, pecans and whipped topping in prepared dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cookie crumbs. Freeze until serving time. Yields 16 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Tie tea, cinnamon, allspice and ground cloves together or throw in loose and strain.
Boil water; steep ingredients.
