Add orange juice, lemon juice, 2 1/2 cups water, sugar and cranberry juice.
Chill.

title: fluffy meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until they are stiff. Add sugar and put on pie. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cinnamon raisin swirl bread
directions: You will need 2 medium (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans, greased.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in one cup of water that has been brought to boil.
Saute onion and celery
in butter.
Add soup and can of milk (or mushroom soup) to
onion and celery.
Then add jar of cheese spread.
Simmer for a
minute or so, then add thawed broccoli and rice and season to
taste.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a moderate oven
Makes
approximately
10 servings and can be made ahead of time.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in bowl. Mix in flour, oatmeal, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake
at 350° for twenty minutes or until edges start to brown.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In
a
heavy
saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand
and	margarine.
Remove
from
heat.
In a large bowl, combine
nuts
and marshmallows. Stir in chocolate mixture. Spread in
a
9-inch pan lined with waxed paper. Chill 2
hours or until firm.
Remove from pan. Peel off waxed paper. Cut in squares.
Makes 40 squares.

title: fried rice
directions: In a large heavy frypan or wok, heat oil and brown meat slightly.
Push aside and saute vegetables a few minutes.
Remove from pan.
Chop bacon and brown until crisp.
Scramble eggs and remove from pan.
Add rice, sorta sear.
Keep stirring until rice is all seared.
Add meat, eggs and bacon and season with spices. If too dry, add 1/2 cup of water and soy sauce.
Be sure to stir up well.
Too much soy will make it salty, more can be added at the table according to taste.

title: buttered baked potato slices
directions: Wash potato. Cut into thin slices with skin still on it.
Lay on aluminum foil.
Put onion slices and butter throughout potato. Wrap these in aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper as desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onion on low heat.
Drain grease.
Add tomato rice soup; cook a few minutes on low heat.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling, salted water in large saucepan, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain, saving 1 cup of the liquid.
Saute onions and green peppers in the butter until soft (in saucepan).
Stir in the chicken soup and the 1 cup of saved liquid.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Parmesan cheese and corn meal. Dip eggplant in melted margarine.
Roll in cornmeal mixture. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with marinara sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Shake well before using. Makes about 2 cups.

title: colcannon(irish potatoes and cabbage)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Saute cabbage and green onions in margarine until tender.
Mash potatoes with milk.
Add more milk if needed.
Stir in cabbage mixture and salt and pepper.

title: easy baked chicken and potato dinner for two
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Spray baking dish, 13x9x2-inch, with cooking spray.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill first 3 ingredients, then mix in a bowl.
Just before serving, add chilled 7-Up.
May add cherries to decorate or sherbet.

title: chicken soft tacos
directions: Spray nonstick skillet lightly with spray.
Slice chicken into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Cut onions into eighths.
Saute the chicken and onion over medium heat until chicken is cooked throughout. Add picante sauce.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Evenly divide chicken mixture between the 2 tortillas.
Warm tortillas in the microwave.
Stuff tortillas.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add milk, eggs and vegetable oil; stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice the potatoes.
Chop the celery and onions medium fine. Add celery seed and pickle juice.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Be sure you use enough mayonnaise to make it moist.

title: apple-crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour pie filling into prepared crust. Mix together oats, flour, sugar and butter.
Spread evenly over top of pie filling.
Bake for 40 minutes or until top is evenly browned.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Place unthawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add salt. Pour milk over potatoes; sprinkle cheese over top.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with foil and bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, flour, eggs, water, 1/2 box of strawberries and cooking oil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup, tuna, corn meal, egg and onion.
Make into patties.
Brown patties in oleo.
Stir in remaining soup and milk in skillet drippings to make gravy.

title: fernandez family pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Place rice on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix, saving about 1 tablespoon.
Place chops on top of rice.
Arrange mushrooms and pimientos around chops.
Add 3 cups of hot water, including the mushroom liquid.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness of chops.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except chips until well blended.
Spoon dough onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Let cookies set on sheets before removing.
(Add chocolate chips to batter before baking, if desired, about 6 ounces.)

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in butter until tender.
Stir in chili sauce.
Combine all but 1/2 cup of this mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into loaf.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Gradually add dry ingredients and mix.
Fold in nuts, if desired. Pour into a prepared loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water; stir over medium heat until sugar melts.
When it starts to boil, cover for 3 minutes.
Remove lid and cook to hard ball.
Pour over whites (beaten stiffly), salt and vanilla in mixer.
Beat by hand until ready to drop.

title: butter crisps
directions: Cream butter; add flour, sugar and cornstarch.
Cream well. Divide into 4 portions.
Wrap each in foil.
Chill thoroughly. Shape into small balls.
Work quickly with one portion at a time. Keep other portion in fridge.
Flatten with fork and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla and milk.
Sift flour and soda together and blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Then simmer for a little while.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Put meat in freezer for at least 1 hour; it will be easier to slice.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Heat oil.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and ginger.
Saute until garlic is golden brown.
Add steak and brown.
Remove.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Return steak to pan.
Add soy sauce, sugar, bouillon and chestnuts.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to pan.
It will thicken.
Add green onions.
Simmer about 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and yeast in large bowl.
Heat until very warm the water, buttermilk and shortening.
Add gradually to dry ingredients, beat 2 minutes. Add 3/4 cup flour and beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board, knead 20 to 25 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into circles and place on ungreased pans.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 28 to 30 biscuits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cabbage.
Blend the dressing well, then add to cabbage.

title: ma saya's marinara tomato sauce
directions: Place tomatoes into a saucepan.
Let the tomatoes simmer on medium heat with the lid on.
Stir frequently.
They should simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Most of the tomato juice should evaporate. If you are using whole tomatoes, make sure to crush them.
Chop garlic and basil into small pieces and place them into the pan. Add salt, pepper and crushed red pepper to your taste.
Finally, add the olive oil and let it all simmer uncovered on low heat for another 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally; place tomato sauce on fresh penne pasta.
Buon Appetito!

title: strawberry figs
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand overnight.
Simmer 5 minutes. Place in hot jars and seal.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Place dills in a covered dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and put over dills.
Store in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Mix everything together with a spoon.
Wash your hands and shape mixture into small balls.
Put on plate.
Put in refrigerator until ready to eat.
This is a recipe for kids to make.

title: applesauce cake(delicious)
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Sift together all dry ingredients; mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: blueberry oatmeal nut bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add egg, egg whites, vanilla and bananas.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour and oatmeal.
Be sure to stir mixture while adding flour and oatmeal.
Add almonds. Mixture will be lumpy.
Very gently, fold in blueberries.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Serves 12.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in very large bowl and freeze.
Scrape slush into glass and add 7-Up or orange juice.
(Best with 7-Up.)

title: honey cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt and shortening.
Add eggs, honey, vanilla, soda and water, baking powder and flour.
Roll into balls, walnut size or use spoons to form equal amounts.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla. Continue beating mixture until thick and foamy.
Stir in shredded zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, raisins and nuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture until blended.
Divide batter between 2 greased and flour dusted 5 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Turn out on wire rack.
May be wrapped in foil and put in deep freeze.

title: ham, cheese and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended; gradually stir in milk and dry milk powder.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
In a 2-quart greased casserole, layer half the potatoes, ham cubes and sauce.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: russian potato salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Sprinkle with oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; toss gently but thoroughly.
Add sour cream and toss again.
Adjust seasoning if necessary.
Cover and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.
Delicious and lovely to look at; turns color because of the beet.

title: poppy seed bread(from anne willems)
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until done.
Heat cream, milk and butter; reserve 1/4 cup.
Combine potatoes and cream mixture. Whip until smooth and spoon into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 2 hours before serving, remove and pour reserved cream mixture over the potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6.

title: barbecued meatballs(makes about 60)
directions: Note:
Use chili sauce, not chili without beans.
Heinz makes chili sauce and sells it in a glass bottle.

title: whipped topping(low calorie)
directions: Beat until mixture is thoroughly blended.

title: gingerbread pancakes
directions: Heat griddle or skillet and grease if necessary.
Stir all ingredients until blended.
Pour
a little less than 1/4 cup of batter onto hot griddle. Cook until edges are dry.
Turn and cook until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: emily's imps of satan
directions: Blend together the margarine, cheese and Tabasco.
Add flour and cereal.
Chill at least one hour.
Form into small balls. Place on a baking sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve at room temperature.
They will keep in the refrigerator uncooked or in a tin box after baking.

title: antipasto bowl
directions: Steam asparagus, covered, for 2 minutes. Drain and plunge into ice water. Drain well. Combine the asparagus, mushrooms and the next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. See Antipasto Dressing. Yield: 20 servings (serving size 1/2 cup).

title: special recipe chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Measure out flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Measure sugar, brown sugar and vanilla into large bowl.
Mix until smooth with electric mixer.
Blend in soft margarine.
Then with mixer, blend in eggs, 1 at a time.
After mixture is smooth, blend in flour, a little at a time.
Stir in chips.
Drop onto large cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a big batch.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Whisk together all the ingredients or blend in a food processor or blender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat until light.
Stir in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in pumpkin mixture.
Add water and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.

directions: Preheat oven

out and finish cooling on wire rack.
Add a sprinkling of confectioners sugar or vanilla glaze.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash and soak bean overnight and drain.
Or bring beans and water to a boil and let soak for 1 hour.
Discard soaking liquid and rinse beans under running water.
Place beans in stockpot with ham, onion, potatoes, carrots, celery, garlic, parsley, thyme and bay leaf.
Add water and broth.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Lower heat and simmer for 2 hours or until beans are very soft, adding water as necessary.	Add tomato puree and seasonings and cook for additional 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers that have been crushed and browned in 1 stick of margarine in a frying pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow 2 Samuel 13:8 (beat).
Bake in moderate oven at 350° in 2 layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot ring
directions: Grease 3 or 4 quart ring mold with Crisco.
Pour Wheaties into bottom of mold.
Fold cake mixture on top of Wheaties and bake for 1 hour at 350° in a pan of water.
Let cool.
Unmold and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with celery and green peppers.
Remove from water. After cooling, mince chicken.
Combine minced chicken, olives and mushrooms.
Return to broth.
Add cooked spaghetti and can of chopped tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add grated cheese half hour before serving.
Cook slowly with salt and pepper to taste.
(If dish is to be taken out, then pour all into a large casserole before adding cheese.)

title: chili pie(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Place Fritos corn chips in a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and half of grated cheese on the Fritos.
Pour chili over onion and cheese.
Top with the remaining chips and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hidden valley hot potato salad
directions: While potatoes are still warm, gently toss with onions, bacon and salad dressing. Dust with pepper or paprika, garnish with chives. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4-6.

title: butter and nut flavored pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening for 10 minutes at high speed.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix well (about 2 minutes).
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add flavor and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: peppered shrimp
directions: Devein shrimp.
Place in bowl and add Worcestershire sauce and wine; turn and coat thoroughly.
Heat oil in wok; add garlic. Strain shrimp (hold sauce).
Combine all dry seasonings in shallow plate.
Toss shrimp to coat.
Add shrimp to wok and cook over high heat for 2 minutes.
Add scallions.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Keep tossing.
Remove to serving dish.
Add basting sauce to wok and wine mixture; pour into small bowl and serve as dipping sauce.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese to onion after removing from stove.
Blend muffin mix, egg, milk and corn; don't beat, just mix.
Put batter in 9 x 9-inch buttered pan, spread onion mixture over batter and top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 25 minutes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage. Slice zucchini into thin slices; spread over top of sausage.
Cook until tender, then spread slices of cheese over.
Cook until melted through.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; cool and slice.
Heat butter, chicken soup, sour cream and onion.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Salt mixture to taste, and spread in a greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and melted butter.
Cover with plastic wrap, and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion in Dutch oven; brown and drain. Stir in sauce mix from Hamburger Helper, water, basil, salt, pepper and tomatoes with liquid.
Break up tomatoes with fork. Heat to boiling.
Stir in vegetables and macaroni.
Cover and cook until vegetables are done and macaroni is tender.
(Very good.)

title: six layer vegetable dinner
directions: Put shortening in bottom of large casserole; arrange meat and vegetables in layers listed.
Season as you go.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: potatoes italiano
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Oil 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Combine 2 cheeses, reserving some for topping.
Arrange
potatoes,
tomatoes
and
onion
slices
in layers;
sprinkle
each layer with cheese and seasonings.
Dot with
butter
and
bake,
uncovered,
at
400° for 30 minutes. Remove
from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour hawaiian meatballs
directions: For wet mixture, mix together dry spaghetti sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, white vinegar, mustard, Coke and pineapple juice. Stir together, then take 1/4 cup of wet liquid; place remainder of mixture in large pot on top of stove and let simmer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into marble size balls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Fill canner with tomatoes which have been run through the blender; simmer for several hours, removing water as it gathers. Then add peppers, onions and onion salt.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add tomatoes and continue to simmer until reduced to about 1/2 the beginning size or until desired thickness is reached.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars; seal. Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, cover and refrigerate.
Stir it well for two days, once each day.
On the fourth day, mix well and form into 5 rolls, 1 1/2-inches thick.
Lay on broiler rack.
Bake 6 hours at 140°.
Turn rolls once each hour.
Use hour hands as it isn't hot.

title: chess pie
directions: Stir all together and pour into pie crust. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: fluffy pumpkin praline pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Melt and cook 30 seconds.
Mix cold milk with vanilla pudding.
Whisk with wire whisk until smooth.
Consistency will be very thick. Add pumpkin and spice. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread pecan mixture in crust.
Cool.
Add pumpkin mixture.
Refrigerate for approximately 4 hours until set. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: nut cracker sweets
directions: Put the margarine or butter in a saucepan on low heat.
Melt the margarine or butter.
Take pan off the stove.
With a wooden spoon, stir in brown sugar; mix well.

title: diet dip
directions: Put cottage cheese, lemon juice, salt and dill in blender. Blend at low speed about 4 minutes or until smooth.
Pour into dish.
Serve with celery and carrot sticks or other raw vegetables.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: corn custard
directions: Beat eggs; add corn, sugar and cornstarch.
Also add milk. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered dish.
Put melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dip for fruits
directions: Cut whole pineapple in half.
Scoop off the inside.
Fill with dip.
Serve dip with chunks of pineapple, strawberries, apple slices, cherries and peaches.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine the brown sugar, butter and sweet potatoes.
Then add the ginger, cinnamon, evaporated milk, salt and nutmeg.
Beat the egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Fold into the potato mixture. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
You can sprinkle a small amount of sugar and nutmeg on top before baking, if desired.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt, soda and baking powder.
Sift again. Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and orange juice to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add raisins, nuts, apples and orange peel.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: With fork break up cranberry sauce.
Blend in crumbs.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile lightly in sherbet glasses.
Refrigerate for 60 minutes.

title: butter pecan bread
directions: Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cooney's chops
directions: Place chops in heavy skillet on medium/high until brown. Remove momentarily.
Add the rice to the skillet with the spice pack.
Add 1 can bouillon or soup.
Mix well.
Return chops to skillet.
Spread a little rice and water over chops.
If desired, add onions or green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: b.l.t.  burgers a la make-a-better burger
directions: In a large bowl, combine Make-A-Better Burger with water.
Add beef, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and tomato.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into 8 oblong burgers; wrap with bacon and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Grill or broil, turning occasionally, until done. Serve with lettuce on rolls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tootsie roll cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; mix well.
Lightly butter a 10-inch round, 2-inch deep cake pan. Press crumb mixture evenly into bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese with remaining 1 1/4 cups sugar until smooth, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla, beating well until smooth.
Melt Tootsie Rolls in top of a double boiler.
Stir in cream, then add to cream cheese mixture, mixing well.
Pour over crust.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 2 hours or until center is set.
Cool, then chill several hours before serving.

title: squirrel or rabbit gravy
directions: Inspect squirrels, making sure all buckshot has been removed. Put cut up squirrel and 1/2 cup salt in a bowl of water (not aluminum) with the juniper berries; soak overnight in refrigerator. Drain off water, discard berries and rinse squirrel.
Coat squirrel or rabbit as you would to fry chicken.
Put grease and oil in a cast-iron skillet and heat, adding a few shakes of pepper.
Add squirrel or rabbit; brown nicely.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon until slightly crisp.
Set aside. Pour 1/8 to 1/4 cup bacon drippings over bread crumbs. Set aside.
In 2 tablespoons bacon drippings, saute onion and green pepper until tender. Stir in corn and bacon.
Put into a 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad(6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in an 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round casserole or individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until mixture is heated and cheese is melted.

title: crispy fried catfish
directions: Sprinkle catfish with salt and pepper. Place in a shallow dish. Add hot sauce. Marinate 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator. Place cornmeal in a plastic bag. Drop in catfish, one at a time, and shake until completely coated. Fry in deep hot oil (375°) until fish float to the top and are golden. Drain well. Makes 6 servings.

title: deep fried hot peppers
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Cut ends off of peppers and take out seeds.
Mix hamburger, sausage, onion, garlic salt and pepper together.
Stuff peppers.
Roll peppers in flour and then dip into eggs.
Fry in electric skillet in oil for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
After browning turn over and brown other side.
You will need more eggs as you need them.
Change oil in skillet as necessary.

title: great pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time to well creamed mixture, beating after each.
Mix dry ingredients separately.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to other mixture, beating well.
Add vanilla and beat for a couple of minutes.
Put mixture into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.

title: three-pepper relish
directions: Preparation:
15 minutes, plus 30 minutes marination.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and onion into small pieces.
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble.
In a bowl, combine broccoli, onion, bacon and sunflower seeds.
In a smal bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Stir together.
Pour dressing on salad and mix until everything is coated.

title: quail bake
directions: Line buttered 9 x 15-inch dish with Canadian bacon.
Top with seasoned quail wrapped in bacon.
Combine soup and sour cream; spoon over quail.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sharon's tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easy, healthy stir-fry
directions: Be daring!
Having a night when you don't want to cook? It's hot and you don't want to be stuck in the kitchen? Well, this is the dish to whip up in about 15 minutes.
Raid your refrigerator and find those vegetables that you bought and just have not gotten around to cooking. Anything goes!

title: toss salad dressing
directions: Combine and beat 2 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in Crisco slowly.
Add meat and saute until browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in a covered dish at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: gorton's(meat spread)
directions: In a medium pot over medium heat, place pork, onions, water to barely cover, salt and pepper.
Stir frequently.

title: crab gumbo
directions: Brown flour.
Add sausage and chicken to flour.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove excess grease leaving 1/8 of it.
Add onions and peppers.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add water.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add whole crab, crab meat and shrimp.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add seasoned salt.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: france chicken parisienne
directions: Arrange slightly cooked broccoli spears in large casserole; cover with chicken.
Combine butter or margarine, flour and milk in saucepan over low heat; stir until thickened.
Add cream, Worcestershire sauce, cheese and sherry; mix until blended. Season to taste.
Pour over chicken-broccoli layers and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground steak
directions: Sprinkle sugar into bottom of old black skillet.
Break meat up in pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover.
Stir occasionally until meat has crumbled.
Brown slightly.
Add flour and stir thoroughly.
Add boiling water and stir thoroughly.
Cover again. Simmer until served.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and add oats; set aside.
Cream together brown sugar, sugar and oil.
Beat eggs; add to sugar and oil.
Alternate oat mixture and flour mixture.
Beat well in between.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tart tomato mold(good with pork and chicken)
directions: Strain tomatoes; reserve juice.
Bring juice to boil. Dissolve gelatin in it.
Put tomatoes and other vegetables (from can) in chopping bowl; chop fine.
Combine vegetables and gelatin. Add lemon juice (proportion juice to your taste or meat to be served).
Oil 4 to 6 individual or small molds; pour salad into them.
Chill for 4 hours.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serve with mayonnaise or sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.
(Fits well in Tupperware mold.)

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: You will need 1 Bundt pan.

title: yummy chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard the wing tips.
Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper and dredge in flour lightly.
Melt butter and olive oil in skillet and saute wings over moderately high heat, turning them after 5 minutes.
When browned, remove from skillet with slotted spoon.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, pour into long Pyrex dish.
Put corn flakes on top and then the 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental scallop skillet
directions: Rinse scallops and drain.
Cut large scallops in half.
In saucepan combine scallops, chicken broth, celery, and green onion. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce; add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Add Chinese vegetables, mushrooms, and salt; heat through.
Stir in almonds.
Serve over hot cooked rice or warmed chow mein noodles.
Pass additional soy sauce if desired.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled bottom.
Combine puddings and milk. Beat until smooth and spread over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and decorate with chocolate curls.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: pear conserve
directions: Mash pears after peeling and coring.
Add juice of orange and 1/2 of orange peel, grated (optional), also pineapple.
Add pectin to 4 cups of this mixture.
Mix well.
Add the sugar and stir well. Cook until it clings to fork.
The maraschino cherries are optional, too.
Cut up and add to cooked mixture.

title: pasta with chicken and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion, tomatoes, carrots and fennel in oil.
Brown chicken.
Fold into each other.
Mix into prepared fettuccine. Enjoy.

title: tubetti with clams and sausage
directions: Brown the sausage in the olive oil over high heat 1 minute. Add the garlic and the cleaned whole clams and saut for another minute. Deglaze the pan with the white wine and the pepper flakes, then cover the pan for 1 to 2 minutes or until the clams "pop". Remove the cooked clams and transfer to serving dish. Add the chicken stock, the cooked white beans and the cooked tubetti pasta and heat through. Add the Parmesan and finish the base with chopped parsley and chopped basil. Pour mixture over clams and serve with crusty Italian bread.
tags: drizzle of extra virgin olive oil

title: jello delight
directions: Follow directions for jello.
Chill until set.
With a mixer set on low, break up set jello.
Beat in Cool Whip until well blended.
Chill until set again.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Cut in shortening until like coarse meal.
Add milk; stir just enough to blend.
Turn out on a floured board.
Divide in half.
Roll out each piece and cut in fourths. On each piece, add a few apples; sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and a small piece of butter.
Fold all corners to middle and pinch edges together.
Place in large baking dish.

title: donut muffins
directions: Sift and combine dry ingredients.
Add the egg, oil and milk; mix until well blended.
Pour into a lightly greased muffin tin. Sprinkle each muffin with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon; put a dot of butter on each.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: refried bean casserole
directions: Divide ingredients into three parts; beans, sour cream and Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Place all ingredients into crock-pot and cook on high for 1 hour. Reduce heat to low and cook 4 to 8 hours.
Yields 12 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Chill batter for 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough into small portions; roll on lightly floured surface 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes; place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with colored or white sugar before baking.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
I usually frost with Buttercream Icing for holidays.
These are great for icing, yet they don't get hard.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Sift together the flour and the salt.
With a pastry blender or fork cut in the butter and the cream cheese until well blended. Wrap the dough in foil and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, roll out to 1/8 inch thickness, using as little flour as possible.
Cut into squares or rounds.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly; stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased loaf pans and bake at 375° until done in center, approximately 1 hour.
Yields 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: banana nut-chip bread
directions: Cream soda, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, flour, salt, baking powder, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add nuts, chips and coconut.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Place 1/2
of cookie crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix other ingredients.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle the other 1/2 of crumbs on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: pear pie
directions: Make pie shell; brush with margarine.
Slice 5 pears into shell.
Mix the margarine, egg, sugar and vanilla; spread this mix over pears.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: liz's stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and drain excess fat juices.
Cook rice according to instructions and add instant rice during preparation.
Put in large pot all remaining ingredients with meat and rice mixture. Cook for about 1/2 hour on medium temperature.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and shape into balls with hands.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin together. Dip balls with two-tine fork or toothpicks into chocolate.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: fantasy ambrosia
directions: Toss bananas with orange juice, drain, reserving juice.
Layer fruit in serving bowl, chill.
Combine mayonnaise, juice and sugar.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over fruit and garnish with toasted coconut.

title: jam pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour, then cream with the butter.
Add the eggs and beat until smooth, then add the jam and mix.
Pour into an 8-inch pastry-lined pie pan and bake about 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce the heat to 325° and bake until the filling is firm.
A delicious pie especially with thick strawberry preserves!

title: ham and cheese ring
directions: Mix butter, mustard and lemon juice. Add onion, parsley, ham, broccoli and cheese. Arrange crescent rolls in a circle with the points out like a star and the center overlapping.
Place mixture in center and fold tht ends of the rolls into the middle.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad tivoli
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill 6 hours or more.
Makes 8 cups.

title: estalene french's sweet potato pone
directions: Drain yams and mash with potato masher.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Mix into potatoes, then add pecans and butter.
Mix well, then bake in large rectangular Pyrex baking dish.
Fills two 2-quart baking dishes.
Bake at 350° until done and lightly browned on top, approximately 30 minutes.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine in open roasting pan in preheated 250° oven. Stir in seasonings.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed mushroom crowns(american)
directions: A welcome and convenient addition
to any buffet table, these mushroom crowns are piled
high
with
a
creamy cheese-chicken mixture.

title: charley's favorite magic fruit cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Butter again.
Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 2 hours or until center springs back and top is golden brown.
Cool.
Turn out and remove paper.

title: popular salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in the blender, liquify.
Store in refrigerator.
Excellent with all salad greens.
Popular with everyone.

title: apple krisp
directions: Place sliced apples in greased 8 or 9-inch square baking dish. Mix together flour, baking powder and seasonings.
Add egg and mix with fork until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: In a large bowl by hand, mix dry ingredients into butter until thoroughly mixed.
Knead a wee bit.
Flatten dough by hand (do not use rolling pin) to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.

title: foglio wedding soup
directions: Put broth, white meat, celery and parsley in a large soup pot and cook for 30 minutes.
Mix thawed spinach, eggs and cheese and drop into boiling soup.
Cook for 15 more minutes.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, soup and milk.
Place 2 slices of bread at bottom of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Lay slice of cheese on each bread slice; layer with half the shrimp.
Add salt & pepper. Make another layer, ending with bread and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes until brown and puffy.
Can also be made with tuna or chicken.

title: lasagna
directions: "Put macaroni in hot water.
Stir it around.
Put the top on it and let it get real hot.
Put the cheese in and let it set for 30 seconds.
Then stir it around.
Then you eat it."

title: pilau ("plow")
directions: Fry onions in oil until soft.
Add raw rice; fry until light golden brown.
Add raisins and cook for 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, cinnamon, salt, cardamom and cloves.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add cooked chicken and almonds.
Cook until rice absorbs all liquid.
Serve with plain yogurt on the side.

title: dumplings for chicken broth
directions: Mix flour and salt; add eggs.
Pour a little hot broth at a time and mix well.
Pour this on floured waxed paper and knead thoroughly.
Divide into 4 pieces; roll each piece paper thin and cut in strips about 1-inch wide.
Drop into rapidly boiling chicken broth.
Cook until done, about 15 minutes.

title: out of this world fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and marshmallow cream.
Stir in food coloring.
Serve with fresh fruit or vanilla wafers. Refrigerate.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: meatless tomato sauce
directions: In a saucepan, place olive oil and garlic cloves.
Cook slowly; remove garlic when they turn light brown.
Add tomatoes. Sprinkle salt, pepper, sweet basil and parsley into sauce.
Cook over low-medium heat for 30 minutes.
This quick sauce is excellent with linguine.

title: mustard fried catfish
directions: Pat fish dry with paper towels; set aside.
In heavy skillet, heat 1 inch of oil to 350° or until a 1-inch bread cube turns golden brown in 65 seconds.
In a medium bowl, combine mustard, eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding Cool Whip last.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and maple flavoring.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt, alternately with milk.
(I usually dump them in together at low speed, scraping sides of bowl often.)
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add all other ingredients in same pan spaghetti was cooked in.
Now, pour into baking dish (medium size) and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes with scrub brush.
Cut into wedges.
Melt margarine in
a
long
casserole
dish.
Dip
potato wedges in melted margarine.
Put
flour,
cheese,
Shake 'n Bake mix and Accent into a
Ziploc plastic bag.	Shake half the wedges at a time in the coating mix.
Place wedges in the remainder of the melted margarine and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine raisins, baking soda and boiling water.
Cover; do not mix.
Let stand overnight (9 to 10 hours).
In the morning, mix flour, sugar, salt and oil together with spoon (batter is thick). Finish mixing by hand.
Pour over raisins.
Fill 3 (1 pound) coffee cans 1/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage, apple, raisin slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apple and raisins.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar together.
Stir into cabbage mixture.

title: oklahoma baked beans
directions: In small skillet, fry bacon.
Remove and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper until onion becomes transparent.
Drain on paper towel.
In large bowl, combine ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, barbecue seasoning, liquid smoke and dry mustard.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mini turkey loaf
directions: In a small skillet, saute the onion, green pepper and mushrooms in oil until tender. Remove from heat, cool. In a large bowl, combine the vegetables,2 tablespoons apple juice, garlic powder, onion powder, salt and pepper. Crumble turkey over mixture and mix well. Shape into a loaf, put into 11X7X2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick spray. Bake for 40-45 minutes or until meat is no longer pink and meat thermometer reads 165°.

title: reuben spread
directions: In a slow cooker, combine first 5 ingredients and mix well. Cover and cook on low for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm with rye bread.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain and mix together canned vegetables.
Chop pepper, onions, celery and pimento and add to other vegetables.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture, add salt, flour with buttermilk and vinegar.
Do not beat hard.
Hand mix, just to blend.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Let steep, then remove spices.
Serve hot.

title: chicken a la king(serves 6)
directions: Cook and stir pepper and mushrooms in margarine over medium heat 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in half and half, broth and reserved liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and pimentos. Great to keep warm in crock-pot.

title: cabbage pudding
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces; cook in salt water until tender.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sugar, cheese, soup and half and half.
Mix in 1 cup of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cracker crumbs on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and thick.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Pull out center of bread and put mixture into center of bread.
Break off chunks of bread for dipping.

title: mexican cornbread(for barbecue)
directions: Combine milk and eggs; add meal, salt, peppers, corn, onion, garlic and soda.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased, hot cast-iron skillet.
Add some cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Top with cheese.
Garnish with green pepper and pimento.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waverly cookies
directions: In a small pan, melt butter and slowly add the sugar, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking on medium heat until boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes, until thick.
Line a jelly roll pan with the crackers.
Pour boiling sauce on crackers and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until slightly brown.
Cut apart while hot and separate on waxed paper.

title: 1 2 3 pie
directions: Mix and put into baked flour or graham cracker crust.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, saute onions in 2 tablespoons olive oil, until transparent.
Add mushrooms; saute 2 minutes more.
Pour in a bowl; set aside.
Drain pasta.
Add remaining olive oil and butter to saute pan.
Add pasta to hot oil and butter.
Fry until pasta is brown.
Don't burn.
Add onions and mushrooms; stir.
Add whipped eggs; stir until eggs are done.
Serve hot.
Season to taste.

title: amish country dinner rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved
yeast;
combine
milk,
water
and
margarine
in saucepan.
Heat
over
low
heat
until liquids are very warm. Margarine does
not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and
beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping occasionally.
Add
2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Stir in additional
flour
to
make a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place in
greased
bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in
warm
place until doubled, about 45 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onions and bacon on medium heat until onions are done and bacon crisp.
Add water, bouillon cubes, potatoes and carrots. Cook until tender.
Add evaporated milk with equal amounts of water and cream corn.
Cook on medium heat until hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done. Cool and shred. Set aside chicken and the broth. Saute mushrooms and onions in butter. Combine mushroom and celery soup in big pot. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, then add mushrooms and onions. Add Velveeta cheese until melted. Boil chicken broth and cook spaghetti until done. Drain and add spaghetti and chicken to your mixture. Mix well and serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Melt oleo. Stir in Crisco and sugar.
Stir well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and soda.
Mix well.
Put teaspoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Moisten the bottom of a glass and dip in extra sugar. Press each cookie. Bake at 325° until edges are light golden. Do not overbake.

title: no bake oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil.
Allow to boil for exactly one minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper with a tablespoon.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat mashed potatoes.
Add melted fat, beaten eggs and milk. Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid.
Dough should be soft, yet firm enough to roll.
Divide dough into four parts. Roll out one part at a time to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter and drop into deep fat (375°).
Fry until a golden brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Shake in a paper bag containing a mixture of sugar and cinnamon or powdered sugar. This makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen doughnuts.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Add rice to melted butter and brown 15 minutes. Add other ingredients and cook 5 minutes. Put all in casserole. Add chicken stock.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Stir gently before serving.
Top with more almonds, if desired.

title: magenta madness
directions: Shred cabbage very fine. Mash the garlic and salt together. Add pepper and mash again.
Mix in the other ingredients and pour over the shredded cabbage.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
This mixture will keep 5 to 6 days or more and it gets better every day!
Makes 8 1/2 cup servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup berries and stir in by hand.
Add rest of berries.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: fish stir-fry with ginger
directions: Mix cornstarch, ground ginger and salt; evenly coat fish.
In a wok, heat oil.
Add fish and stir-fry about 4 minutes, occasionally turning gently, until evenly browned.
In a measuring cup, mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to wok.
Reduce heat so liquid just simmers.
Cover and cook 4 minutes.

title: 5-star salad
directions: Drain real good the mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients.
Use only enough sour cream to hold salad together.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 12.

title: what the heck salad
directions: Pour boiling water into bowl.
Pour in both packages of jello. Stir until dissolved. Chill slightly. Drain pineapple and stir in.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2hours before serving.

title: rotini salad
directions: Boil rotini as directed on package.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: celery salad
directions: Bring pineapple and jello to a boil.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, celery and pecans.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch apple dumplings
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit the baking soda and salt.

title: chalk sticks
directions: Mix paint and water together in the cup.
Slowly add plaster and stir with spoon or wooden stick.
Let mixture harden overnight and peel off the cup.
Have fun with your chalk stick, indoors or out!

title: batter for fried vegetables
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg; stir until smooth. Dip cut up vegetables, such as zucchini, carrots, onion, mushrooms or boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into 1-inch cubes.
Dip into mixture before placing vegetables or meat into hot oil.
Makes a wonderful light and crispy fried vegetable.

title: green beans-corn casserole
directions: Put beans in sprayed baking dish.
Layer corn and beans.
Mix soup, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Pour over corn mixture.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs with butter.
Put on top.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the sugar and bran.
Combine the beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix quickly.
Turn into greased muffin pans and bake in hot oven (425°) for 25 minutes.
Raisins or chopped dried prunes may be added.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Saute in large skillet; stir 10 minutes or more until coated with butter and salt.
Bake on shallow pan at 250° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 20 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.
This may also be put in containers with tight fitting lids and frozen after it has cooled.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put liquid in coffeepot (percolator).
Put sugar, cloves and cinnamon in basket.
Perk on cycle.
Serves 12.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Fry and drain bacon. Crumble into small pieces. Brown and drain ground beef. Put bacon and ground beef in a crock-pot. Drain lima, pinto and kidney beans. Add all beans to crock-pot. You can use the bean juice if more liquid is needed. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours. Can be frozen and reheated as necessary.

title: grandma's apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples and nuts, together well. Add apples and nuts to batter.
(Do all mixing by hand, as batter will be thick and crumbly.)
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check for doneness after 30 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin dijon
directions: Combine water, mustard and soy sauce.
Brush tenderloins with the mustard mixture and oil.
Place tenderloins, fat side up, on a rack, in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is done.
Baste meat while baking.
Serves 6.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Place steak in a bowl with cornstarch, 5 Spice and soy sauce. Mix and let sit 20 minutes to marinate.
Meanwhile, slice florets from stalks, slice the stalks diagonally into thin oval shapes and chop florets in small heads.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet. Add marinated steak, ginger and garlic and fry 3 to 4 minutes. Add pepper, broccoli and onion and fry 2 minutes.
Add sherry and water.
Cover and steam 1 minute.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and corn flakes; melt margarine and pour over top.
Cover with corn flake crumbs.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and mayonnaise together and fold in the potatoes. Put in 9 x 13 pan and sprinkle bacon bits on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet sugar-free pie
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Let soft set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into lined crust.
Refrigerate to finish setting.

title: almond apple wheat bread stuffing
directions: Saute apples, almonds, onions and celery in butter for 5 minutes (stirring frequently).
Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon, poultry seasoning and salt.
Toss together bread cubes and raisins.
Add apple mixture.
Stir egg and 1/3 cup cider together and add to bread mixture.
Add remaining apple cider if a moister stuffing is desired.

title: (no crust) - cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese in mixer. Add 3 eggs, one at a time. Gradually, add 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 almond extract. Bake for 45 minutes in a 325 degree oven - in round 9 inch pan (not greased). Cool slightly, then add 1/2 pint sour cream and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chop fruit. Drain pineapple juice into container. Add pineapple to fruit. Combine sugar and cornstarch in small pan. Add beaten egg and pineapple juice. Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken; set aside and cool. Stir over fruit and chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; place in slow cooker.
Add tomato soup mixed with water.
Add corn, tomatoes, onion, carrots and potatoes.
Turn on high until it gets hot.
Then turn down.
Cook at least 4 hours.
Can cook as long as 8 hours on low setting. This is a complete meal served with salad.
Great for working people!

title: jam cake
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Add flour. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add sugar, butter and flour mixture. Add egg yolks, spices and jam.
Fold in egg whites. Do not beat. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done, but no less than 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on prepared pizza dough.
Add pizza sauce. Add toppings: pepperoni, cooked hamburger, cooked Canadian bacon, etc.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over toppings.
Bake in a 400° oven until crust is brown (lightly) and cheese is melted.
You can use low-fat cream cheese and shredded cheese.

title: sopa de fido
directions: Preheat large skillet to 300°.
Melt shortening, brown vermicelli until brown.
Stir occasionally adding beef and cook until beef loses red color.
Stir in next 8 ingredients; add tomatoes and water.
Stir.
Set temperature to 200°.
Simmer 35 minutes.
Cover top with cheese slices and cook 5 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Place all ingredients on bread and melt on lower rack of oven at 350°. Good for Diet Watchers.
Measure accurately!

title: peach bowl punch
directions: Place peaches in punch bowl.
Pour brandy and sauterne.
Let stand.
At serving time add champagne.
Top each cup with mint sprig.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini and drain excess water.
Add the bottom of salad dressing, salad spices and the remaining ingredients.
Chill 6 to 12 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
If dough is soft, cover and chill.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger.
Immediately remove from baking sheet; cool.
Spread with glaze.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for vegetables.
Place vegetables in a large container and pour marinade sauce over them.
Stir container once or twice during marinating time (4 to 6 hours or can be a little longer).

title: "kak's" dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese.
Whip the cream.
Mix with cheese and sugar mixture.
Line cake pan with crumb mixture of vanilla wafer crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press down.
Pour cheese mixture over crust, then pour cherry pie mix over cheese mixture. Chill.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, mustard, relish and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stir in potato chips.
Split burger rolls; spread with butter.
Toast bottom halves in oven, with butter side up.
Divide tuna mixture among toasted buns.
Spread to the edges.
Broil about 5 minutes or until heated through.
Place remaining halves, buttered side up and broil last 2 or 3 minutes.
Place on first layer.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine in crock-pot.
For variety, you can also add cream of mushroom soup or use Ro-Tel instead of taco sauce.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate chips, milk and butter on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate chips are completely melted.
Spread evenly in the bottom of crust.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes until chocolate is firm. Arrange sliced bananas over the chocolate.
Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pudding mixes and beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and refrigerate 4 hours until set.

title: dream salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup milk until creamy.
Add remaining 3/4 cup milk and beat well.
Stir in pineapple and carrots, then dry pudding.
Beat 1 minute only.
Chill in shallow pan or mold.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar, add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and baking pwd., add to dry ingredients the sour cream and vanilla.
Spread 1/2 of batter in 10 by 14 in. pan.
Blend together the filling:
1/2 c. sugar, 1/3 c. brown sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon, 1 c. chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 of filling over batter. Add remaining batter and sprinkle remaining filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 30- 35 mini.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter; add to soup in pan or bowl.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put mixture of 1/3 butter and soup.
Layer all rice, then add 1/3 more of soup.
Place chicken, meat side down, on top of soup, then add the other 1/3 of the soup.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Put in oven before leaving for church; add a salad and bread and the Sunday dinner is ready.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place ribs in baking dish, meaty side up. Roast for 30 minutes.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat and pour over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until tender (2 hours or longer), basting 2 to 3 times during cooking.

title: mild dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to boil.
Meanwhile, fill sterilized jars with washed, medium sized pickles, garlic and couple sprigs of dill. Fill jars with hot liquid and immediately seal with sterilized lids.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Put in baking cups.
Bake for 20 minutes; top with fruit.
Makes 24.

title: ginger chicken wings
directions: Early in the morning cut the chicken wings at the joints (save tips for soup).
Put wings in a glass bowl.
Cover the wings with a mixture of half tamari, half saki plus ginger.
Marinate chicken in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Remove wings from marinade and preserve mixture (can store in refrigerator).
Roll wings in cornstarch and deep fry in canola oil until golden brown.

title: fruit cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl stir together the egg, milk and butter, then stir them into the dry ingredients to make a lumpy batter.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon the
batter
into greased muffin tins, filling them about 2/3 full. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix by hand except sugar and eggs.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef, onions and garlic; drain. Stir in vegetable juice, mushrooms, tomato paste and seasoning. Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: one day quick root beer
directions: For 1 Gallon Root Beer:
Fill a gallon jug with warm water after the rest of the ingredients have been put in.
Let stand in the sun for 4 hours, then chill.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits except apricots.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Arrange fruits in layers in a large, shallow baking dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend brown sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients. Serve with fruits of all types and/or Ritz crackers.

title: fried apples
directions: Cut apples into wedges.
In skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add apples; cook about 5 minutes, shaking pan gently. Turn apples over; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cook another few minutes, shaking pan.
Serve warm.

title: ma's pyraga(lithuanian sweet bread)
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and butter and pour hot milk over mixture.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Melt yeast in 1/4 cup warm (not hot) water and add.
Add eggs.
Gradually stir in flour until dough is stiff enough to work.
Add raisins.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth, onion and spaghetti in a large bowl.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex with cooking spray.
Place mixture in Pyrex.
Sprinkle with cheese generously.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Put on top of cooled crust.
Beat together pudding and milk and put on top of cream cheese layer.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on butter brickle chips or Heath chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a saucepan, heat chicken broth until bubbly.
In another saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken broth, cream, salt, pepper and parsley.
Stir until smooth. Return to heat.
Stir in chicken or turkey, cut in small pieces, mushrooms and spaghetti.
Spoon into a 3-quart baking pan. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine soup with broccoli. Rub chicken with additional butter. Sprinkle with salt.
Lay chicken over broccoli mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; mix well with graham cracker crumbs. Mash in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bananas and soak in pineapple juice for 5 minutes.
Mix 2 sticks of butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Beat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer bananas, 1/2 sugar mixture, drained pineapple, 1/2 sugar mixture and Cool Whip. Top with nuts and cherries.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine rice, sauerkraut, the cooked corned beef and 1/2 of the Swiss cheese.
Stir in Thousand Island dressing.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Top with rye bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Bake on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Spread on 1 pint of pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with 1 pound ground beef (browned) and top with any kind of cheese you prefer.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Save the broth chicken is cooked in and cook everything but the peas until done. When vegetables are done, pour the peas in. If there is a lot of juice, drain peas first.
Put the chicken in with vegetables.
Mix flour and water together, about 1 cup water and a heaping tablespoonful of flour.
Shake this in a jar or shaker and mix with vegetables until desired thickness.
Pour in a baking dish.
Cover with biscuits and bake in a 450° oven until biscuits are brown.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Place patties in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream soup with sour cream, onions and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of potato

title: malted hot chocolate microwave(total cooking time:  5 minutes)
directions: In 4 cup glass measure, combine milk and malted milk powder; mix well.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Heat at High for 5 minutes, until hot.
Ladle into 4 heat-proof mugs; garnish with Marshmallow Creme.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy mexican skillet
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in macaroni and all remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serves 5.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts according to package directions.
Drain; cut large pieces in half.
Combine salad dressing, garlic, onion, parsley flakes and dill weed.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours.

title: m&m bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together oats, flour, nuts, brown sugar, soda and salt; add melted butter, mixing well.
Pour 3/4 of this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat the molasses mixture a minute or so, then pour it into the flour mixture.
Stir it just until you can't see any more flour.
Butter (grease) an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Pour the batter into it and bake about 30 minutes.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat yolks and egg well.
Beat in water and salt.
Stir in flour with spoon (dough is stiff).
Knead in last of the flour. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each piece as thin as possible on lightly floured working area.
Place on paper towels until dough is dry enough for cutting with a thin, sharp knife.
Cut into strips of desired widths (1/8-inch to 3/8-inch).
Shake strips and allow to dry before using, storing or freezing in sealed container.
Cook in desired amount of chicken or turkey broth until tender.
Makes 6 cups or 10 ounces.

title: mountain bean stew
directions: Rinse beans and soak in cold water overnight. Drain. Add 2 quarts water, salt and meat bone. Simmer 3 hours and remove bone. Leave meat in pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: "death by chocolate" brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Blend dry ingredients and fold into egg mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Okay to substitute margarine for butter.)

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies; measure 1/2 cup and set aside.
Mix the remaining crumbs with margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 container of whipped topping and spread over cookie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Prepare pudding mix according to directions on package.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Spread second container of whipped topping over pudding and sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Blend and shape into balls. Fry in fat or bake in oven as you choose. Blend remaining soup with one cup water and pour over browned meatballs. Simmer covered about 40 minutes. You can also bake covered at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Melt caramels with milk in small microwavable bowl at High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; stir mixture until smooth.
Pour into crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until smooth.
Stir in applesauce, vanilla and cinnamon. Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Spread mixture over caramel layers in crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping, apple slices and melted caramels, if desired. Store any leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt, pepper and paprika. Place chicken in crock-pot.
Mix white wine, soup and mushrooms until well combined, mixing in sour cream.
Cook on low; pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (or high for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours, adding sour cream during the last 30 minutes).
Serve sauce over chicken with rice or noodles.
This may be doubled for 5-quart crock-pot.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bisque
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add leeks & mushrooms & cook about 3-4 minutes, until leeks are wilted. Add flour, cook until a bit bubbly, stir until well blended. Add chicken broth - stir constantly until smooth & well blended. Add broccoli florets and cook on medium about 5 minutes. Add shredded cheese & cream. Simmer at bubbly pace 8-10 minutes - stir slowly & fairly frequently until smooth (do not boil!). Serve immediately. Also good reheated.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs, then potatoes.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour to make a stiff, workable dough.
Let rise until dough has doubled in size.
Work dough and spread about 1-inch thick onto baking pans.
Let rise again (about 2 hours).
Punch holes in dough with fingers; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift
together	flour,	sugar, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Add
mayonnaise,
cold water and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) layer
pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Frost as desired.

title: lo-fat cheese ball
directions: Blend all
ingredients except pecans and parsley. Chill for 1 hour in
refrigerator.
Form
into a ball and roll it in the chopped pecans
until
coated. Garnish with parsley sprigs and serve with lo-cal crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 4-cup measurer, stir sugar, corn syrup and salt together. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Stir and cook on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir. Pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet, spreading out quickly. Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: deep dish apple crisp "williams sonoma"
directions: Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish the apples (peeled and sliced), tossed with juice.
Mix the cornstarch, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to apples and toss.
Mix with fingertips until crumbly the flour, brown sugar, pinch of salt and butter. Combine sliced almonds and sprinkle over top of the apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Remove all fat from beef and ham; grind all meats together three times.
Put butter in heavy skillet.
Panfry meats, onion and parsley until light brown.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk, then seasonings.
Cook, stirring until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add sauerkraut and allow to cool.
Roll in small balls (1 teaspoon). Roll in flour, then put into beaten egg and finally roll in fine bread crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat at 375° until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine corn, sour cream, eggs and oil; beat well.
Then combine cornmeal and baking powder.
Stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a greased 10-inch iron skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream of fresh mushroom soup
directions: *You can use milk for a less rich soup.

title: apple crumb flan
directions: Pare apples; slice thinly and mix with the sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Line a large flan pan or a pie pan with crust.
Pack apples down to keep flat.

title: goat cheese appetizer
directions: Place goat cheese on small platter.
Cover with garlic, tomatoes and basil.
Dribble over olive oil.
Serve with crackers.

title: dennis' barbecue
directions: Cook onions and pepper in fat until limp.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly.
Makes an excellent table sauce to serve with brisket.

title: viennese potato cream soup
directions: Add potatoes to water with onion, celery, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender, but not soft.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix with all ingredients. Add cooked and cut up shrimp.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease casserole dish and line with 1/2 of chips.
Heat soups, broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and cheese in large pan or skillet until cheese melts.
Layer chicken and cheese mixtures alternating until all has been used.
Top with remaining chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook round steak in oil, salt and garlic until lightly brown. Add celery, water, soy sauce, consomme, green pepper, red pimentos and green onions. Cook a little. Add bean sprouts last. Thicken. Serve over noodles and rice.
Chicken can be used instead of round steak.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to boiling.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt margarine; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add well beaten eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly before cutting into bars.

title: strawberry and cream squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple, bananas, lemon juice and salt.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over chilled gelatin, spreading in even layer.
Pour remaining gelatin over it.
Chill firm.
Cut into 9 squares and serve on lettuce.
Garnish with dollop of sour cream and a whole strawberry, split in half from top almost to bottom.

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Blend the eggs and add the sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually stir in the milk to which the butter has been added.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with knife in center.
Cool and chill in refrigerator.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
If desired, tie whole spices in cheesecloth or put in tea strainer.
If spices are added loose, strain before serving.
Cover and set on low for 2 to 8 hours.
Serve with ladle.
When on low heat, the cider is kept at a perfect serving temperature.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Combine tomato, onion and green pepper.
Stir together vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Drain well before serving.
Makes 2 cups tomato relish.
This quick relish is great with roast pork and it needs no cooking!

title: a.b.c. bread
directions: Combine and blend all together the oil, sugar and vanilla. Combine and add the applesauce, bananas and grated carrots.
Sift the dry ingredients together.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy (not stiff). Add nuts. Stir until coated. Sift together sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add nuts.
Stir until all are coated.
Pour onto a large cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Stir once midway.

title: coconut gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add brown and white sugars and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with beaten eggs.
Add coconut and gumdrops which have been cut into small bits.
Add rolled oats and vanilla and mix well.
Shape into small balls and press with the tines of a fork.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve shortening, sugar, and salt in boiling water.
Add eggs.
Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Add flour, 3 cups at a time. Sift flour 3 times.
Make early in the morning and let rise a number of times, until about noon.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Make out dough about the size of a walnut.
Place 3 to a Pyrex custard cup.
This makes a cloverleaf roll.
Let rise until the dinner hour.
Bake in a 400° oven.

title: inconceivable pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender at one time.
Blend together.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion with milk.
Blend in flour, egg and salt.
Heat 1-inch of shortening in large skillet until hot.
