Drop tablespoonful of batter into hot fat and brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel.
Serve with warm applesauce.

title: divinity
directions: Place in a pan over low heat, the sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook, without stirring, to 250° (hard ball stage).
Remove from heat and pour into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop on wax paper.
Yields 18 to 24 pieces.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir baking powder and soda in 1 cup flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Then put in bowl and gradually work in enough flour to roll.
Cut and bake in a 375° oven until lightly brown.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in roasting pan and bake for 3 hours at 350°.
Put over noodles or mashed potatoes.
Add 1 can of mushrooms, if desired.

title: super meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of soup, onion soup mix, ground beef, bread crumbs and egg.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape into an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: popcorn balls(from my mother, laura eichhorn egesdal)
directions: Cook sugar, water and 1/3 cup light corn syrup to 250° or hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining syrup and butter. Pour over popcorn; form balls.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, milk, cocoa, salt, vanilla, flour and food coloring.
Mix soda and vinegar and sprinkle over batter.
Mix well.
Bake in layer pans at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour and brown slowly in hot oil. Remove chicken. Discard all but 1 tablespoon oil. Add margarine and remaining seasoned flour (about 1/3 cup), cooking slowly while stirring until just lightly brown. Add onions, celery and garlic; saut until soft, about 5 minutes. Add water or broth and seasonings, stirring well. Return chicken to pot; cover and simmer slowly until chicken is tender, about 30 minutes. Add a few chopped green onions and parsley; remove bay leaf and cook 5 more minutes. Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Add other ingredients.

title: luncheon tostada salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and water; add seasoned salt and beans.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Reserve some tomato wedges, avocado slices and tortilla chips for garnish.
Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl; add hot meat mixture and toss lightly.
Garnish with reserved tomatoes, avocados and chips.
Salad is best served immediately.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin pie mix and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool; refrigerate.
Makes 1 (9-inch) deep dish pie.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan. Stir ingredients except raisins in pan with fork until moistened. Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes. Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.

title: michigan cookies
directions: Beat butter with sugar using a wooden spoon.
Beat in egg. Add dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape dough into balls.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Prepare Beets:
Pull beets.
Cut off tops, leaving a 2-inch stub (color will come out of beet through cut edge; don't break off root for same reason).
Soak beets in water and scrub off dirt. Boil in large pan until beets are cooked through. Rinse in cold water.
Peel skin off beets and cut into chunks, if large. Pack beets into clean pint canning jars.

title: mexican taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco mix and diced tomatoes.
Mix.
Set aside.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of corn bread mixture into pan.
Spread hamburger mix over this.
Cover with remainder of corn bread mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Serve with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream all together and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate at least 3 hours before slicing.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: helen's red potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Boil in water until tender. If necessary, drain off excess water, leaving enough to cover potatoes.
Mix together tomato paste and sour cream.
Stir mixture into potatoes and cook enough to blend and thicken.
Excellent served with meat loaf or hamburgers.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Put in 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Put Swiss cheese on top of onions.
Butter both sides of slices of French bread, then cube 1-inch.
Put on top of cheese.
Mix chicken soup and milk together and pour over bread.
Sit overnight in refrigerator, then bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: golden corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine soup, celery, onion and stuffing.
In a 9-inch greased pie plate, spoon stuffing mixture.
Arrange chicken atop; press lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar, margarine and mustard; spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Garnish with fresh sage, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread marshmallow cream over the cake and let this cool completely.

title: stromboli
directions: Slice bread lengthwise of loaf.
Take out inside of bread leaving the shell.
Be careful not to break outside of bread, leaving a little in the crust.
Brown sausage and ground chuck; drain.
Add Ragu and simmer a few minutes.
Fill both loaf sides with meat sauce.
Cover with cheese.
Put loaf back together.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: sugarless pumpkin bread
directions: In blender, put water, liquid from pumpkin and oil.
Add chopped dates and let stand 30 minutes or longer.
Blend ingredients.
Gradually add nuts, raisins and egg whites.
When completely blended, pour in large mixing bowl and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 75 minutes or until done.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: diabetic bars
directions: To water add oleo.
Chop and add prunes, raisins and dates. Bring to boil; then set aside to cool.
After mixture has cooled, add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 packet Equal sweetener.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Boil corn covered with water.
Simmer 10 minutes after comes to boil.
Drain off water and add margarine, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cut cream cheese in chunks and drop in corn.
Stir until well blended.
This has the taste of old-fashioned fresh fried creamed corn!

title: apricot bars
directions: Cut butter into cake mix/flour.
Add nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Pat 2/3 mixture into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spread apricot preserves over mixture.
Crumble remaining mixture over preserves.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
You may use any of your favorite preserves.

title: deer jerky
directions: Slice deer in thin strips and marinate 24 hours covered in refrigerator.
Take out; pat dry with paper towels.
Place on rack in dehydrator and dry until all the moisture is gone.

title: frozen red punch
directions: Dissolve and stir jello and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Pour into milk container (or any container) and freeze.
Two hours before serving, take out of freezer.
When ready to serve, pour into serving bowl. Add ginger ale and stir.
Punch will be slushy. Serves 30.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well and place in a baking dish.

title: veal special
directions: Pound veal steaks thin.
Dip in egg and Ritz cracker crumbs. Brown quickly in hot skillet.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Top veal with tomato slices.
Combine broth, butter, lemon juice, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Simmer and thicken with cornstarch. Pour over veal and cover. Refrigerate.
Can be made the day before. Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove. Top with cheese. Bake until cheese melts.
May substitute chicken breasts.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute oleo in frying pan, add cooked broccoli and onion and saute about 6 minutes.
Mix soup, milk and water and put in casserole with broccoli, onion and rice; add salt.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onions, bell pepper, garlic, salt and pepper; cook for a few minutes until tender.
Add Prego sauce, simmer for a while.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix eggs, cheese and cottage cheese.
Layer meat mixture, noodles and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: I cook all vegetables separate.
Put in casserole in layers with hamburger on bottom.
Layer the rest as you wish.
Mix cornbread mix and pour on top.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 20 minutes.

title: pistachio squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: dinner for a crowd
directions: Brown meat and onion; add next 4 ingredients and mix well.

title: manicotti with cheese
directions: Mix all except manicotti and spaghetti sauce.
Cook manicotti about 15 minutes (do not overcook).
Drain well.
Take cheese mixture and fill each shell (about 2 tablespoons).
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange manicotti in single layers.
Cover with sauce, then cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix the eggs, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans and stir until completely coated.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk; stir well and pour batter into melted butter.

title: carol's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add oil and eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except additional sugar or sprinkles.
Dough should be covered and chilled several hours or overnight to make handling easier.
Roll into walnut-size pieces and roll in sugar or sprinkles.
Place on a cookie sheet and press with the bottom of a glass which you will need to dip in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade play doh for kids
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Remove from heat; add oil, alum and food coloring.
Stir and add 2 cups of flour.
Use rest of flour if needed to make stiff.
Pour on floured surface.
Knead as you would bread dough until good consistency.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Afterward, store in closed container.
No more refrigeration is necessary.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion, margarine and steak.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together and cook slow until tender.
If desired, just before serving, add 1 cup sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: mexican dip
directions: In an 8-inch square cake pan, spread 1 can of refried beans. Make a 1/4-inch layer of sour cream on top of the beans.
Layer salsa on top of the sour cream.
Layer shredded cheese on top of salsa.
Layer can of black olives on top of cheese.
Layer chopped tomato on top of black olives.
Heat in a 350° oven until warmed through and cheese melts or in microwave.
Add avocado if desired. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken marinated
directions: Great for outdoor cooking.
Make enough to soak chicken in for overnight or 3 to 4 hours.
Use for basting, too!

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend flour and water in saucepan.
Add honey or sugar, and 1 cup blueberries and cinnamon.
Cook over moderate heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then add the 3 cups berries.
Mix do not cook.
Cool slightly.
Place into baked crust.

title: tony's shrimp creole gumbo
directions: Spray cast-iron skillet with Pam.
Place over medium-low heat. Add flour, stirring constantly until brown.
(Do not burn.)

title: best white fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar
until	fluffy.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Mix
part of flour into fruits and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with	baking powder.	Fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add extracts.
Mix
well and fold in fruit and nuts. Pour into greased paper-lined
tube	pan
or small loaf pans. Place in cold oven. Turn
oven on to 250°.
Bake for 3 hours. Cool in pans.
Keep well wrapped (foil is o.k.) and in canister (if you have one) for at least 2 months.

title: onion cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onions in melted margarine.
Mix all ingredients together (reserve 1/2 of the cheese); add cooked onions.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: helen's homemade rolls
directions: Heat milk, water, salt, sugar and oil until hot to touch.
Mix in bowl the flour, egg and yeast.
Pour hot mixture into dry mixture.
Add more flour (up to 3 cups) until mixture is no longer sticky.
Let double in bowl for 1 hour.
Cut into rolls and oil both sides of rolls in pan.
Let rolls double 1 to 2 hours.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° or until brown or bake as loaves at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: bunuelos
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Heat oil to frying temperature.
Put tortilla mix in a bowl.
Add egg and warm water; mix to a consistency where it can be rolled (harder than pie crust).
(Hint:
Add water slowly; you may need only 1/4 cup of water.)
Roll dough as thin as you can; cut in four.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Put in tray and add/shake sugar and cinnamon to cover pastry.

title: caramel ham loaf
directions: Mix meats, soaked bread, eggs, salt and mustard.
In bottom of buttered loaf pan, sprinkle brown sugar and a few cloves.
Pack meat on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: perfect pastry mix
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Place in covered container.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps up to one month.
Makes 7 (9-inch) pastry shells.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute garlic, onion and rice in butter.
Split peppers and stuff with cheese.

title: gourmet peas
directions: Soak tarragon in warm water 10 minutes.
Combine peas, cucumber, salt and tarragon mixture in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice in small saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Serve sauce over hot vegetables.

title: flop cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream eggs and sugar together.
Add oil and Bisquick; mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cake will puff up while cooking.
When it flops down in middle, it's done.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in dish or salad mold.

title: cream puffs
directions: Cook the water, butter and flour until thick and smooth. Cool.

title: mexican fudge(no chocolate)
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy 3-quart pan over low heat.
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Takes quite a while to cook down to testing stage.
After it stops foaming watch closely and stir until it forms a good soft ball.
Set it off heat and let cool for 10 minutes.
Beat until firm.
Spread in greased pan.

title: chocolate eclair delight
directions: Line
an
oblong
baking
dish
with
graham
crackers (lengthwise).
(It will probably
take
2 full graham crackers and 1/2 graham cracker per row,
and
I
usually
have
three rows.) Mix vanilla pudding with milk
(I use skim milk).
When thoroughly mixed, blend in the Cool Whip thoroughly.
Pour 1/2 the vanilla/Cool Whip mixture over
the graham crackers in the pan; put another layer of graham
crackers just like the first layer over the pudding/Cool Whip
mixture,
and
then pour the remaining pudding/Cool Whip mixture
over
the second layer of graham crackers.
On top of
the
second layer of pudding/Cool Whip mixture, put another layer of graham crackers.

title: corn mexicali(serves 4)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add corn, water, salt and pimento.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes on low heat. Serve hot, garnished with bacon bits.

title: simmering scents
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and add water as needed.
Will last two weeks if kept in refrigerator overnight.
After about a week, add vanilla and nutmeg.

title: brown bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and shortening.
Cool and set aside.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 small loaves or 5 (No. 2) cans.
Grease pans well.

title: zesty pickins
directions: Combine dry dressing mix, Parmesan cheese and dill weed; set aside.
Put cereal, nuts and pretzels in 2-gallon bag.
Pour oil over cereal mixture.
Close bag and toss gently.
Add salad dressing mixture.
Toss gently until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Conventional Oven:
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough around bread sticks.
Bake until bacon is cooked.
Remove and let drain, then roll sticks in Parmesan cheese.

title: pear honey
directions: Bring fruit, juice and Sure-Jell to rolling boil.
Add sugar. Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
(Make sure to stir constantly.)

title: prune cake and icing
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and buttermilk, then mix in the rest.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool and cover with Prune Cake Icing.

title: potato chip cookies(yields 60)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Stir in walnuts and potato chips.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: lemon flake pie
directions: Put the water and lemon juice on fire and bring to a boil. Add the jello to this; stir until dissolved and cool.
When beginning to congeal, mix in the ice cream.
Mix with electric mixer until ice cream is smooth.
Add a handful of coconut.
Pour into shell; sprinkle with coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken-pepperidge farm casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water to cover for 1 1/2 hours. Cut up and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Heat broth and butter to boiling and pour over stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Drain and rinse seeds from jalapeno peppers.
Cut peppers in half.

title: carrots canadian
directions: Mix together and cook in a crock-pot until carrots are tender.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush Oreos.
Blend in Cool Whip and pecans.
Freeze overnight.
Kids love this and it's easy for mom!
Can be doubled.

title: potato dish
directions: Dice and cook potatoes (leave on the peel).
Drain water off potatoes and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend sour cream and mayonnaise together and pour over potatoes.
Cube cheese and drop over mixture.
Sprinkle dish with bacon crumbs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350 for about 25-30 minutes.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: In a bowl, drain pineapple reserving juice in a saucepan.
Mix together reserved juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin stirring thoroughly into gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: granny swopes cherry-oat party cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Sift flour with soda and add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts and roll each ball in granulated sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet. Place 1 quarter cherry on each ball and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Mix all together and simmer 30 minutes.

title: holiday quick breads
directions: Basic Bread Batter: Cream 1 cup sugar with 4 tablespoons of shortening.
Add 1 cup milk, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract. Beat well.
Add mixture of 2 cups flour, 3 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate delight dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
Place in stock and cook until almost done.
Add milk, butter and sour cream.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Thicken with potato flakes if necessary.
Serve hot. Garnish with green onions, bacon bits and cheese.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: You will also need a 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: swiss ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In a bowl, gradually add milk to soup, add green pepper and onion.
In a buttered 2 quart casserole alternate two layers each of noodles, ham, cheese and sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add green pepper, scallions and red peppers.
Add creamed corn, buttermilk and eggs. Stir to blend.
Fold in grated cheese, leaving some to be sprinkled on top.
In an oiled baking pan, add mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Arrange half of bread halves in bottom of dish; sprinkle with half of coconut.
Top with remaining bread.
Heat milk, sugar and butter.
Beat egg, vanilla and salt.
Pour milk mixture into eggs, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over bread; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Place filled baking dish into 9 x 13-inch pan and set on oven rack.
Carefully pour boiling water into lower pan (1-inch).
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together well.
Shape into a roll and wrap with foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; cut holes in bottom of foil so fat can drip.
Place on rack in pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins or nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hearty italian-style soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine broth, cabbage, undrained tomatoes, potatoes, carrot, celery, onion, parsley, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in beans and beef or chicken.
Divide among 6 airtight containers or freezer containers.
Store up to 3 days in the refrigerator or 1 month in the freezer.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix with crushed pineapple and juice. Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Place in serving bowl and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: green beans
directions: Stir milk and soup together.
Add green beans and 1/2 of onions.
Pour into baking dish and garnish with rest of onions. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add 10 3/4 ounce can chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: yellow cake mix squares
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: magical pizza
directions: Reserve 20 cookies.
Prepare brownie mix batter according to package directions.
Stir in remaining cookies.
Spread batter in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top of hot brownie.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts, candies and remaining cookies, pressing lightly.
Cool slightly; cut into wedges. Serve warm or cold.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add yeast and buttermilk and knead until well blended.
Roll and cut like biscuits.
Dip in melted butter and fold.
Let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator for days.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: If you do not have veal, use equal amounts of beef and pork. Mix meat together thoroughly; add seasoning, celery and water in which celery was cooked.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Also add bread over which the hot milk has been poured.
If too dry, add more milk.
Form into soft balls, roll in flour and brown in drippings.
Make gravy; pour over balls and bake slowly for 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven.

title: molasses cake with vanilla custard sauce
directions: Combine liquid Butter Buds with boiling water, sugar and molasses.
Sift soda, lite salt, spices and flour.
Add to mixture.
Beat in Egg Beaters.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: souvalaki(greek)
directions: Marinade:
Mix oil, lemon juice, Greek oregano, salt, garlic powder, Accent, and pepper.

title: new orleans style red beans
directions: Wash beans; place in large heavy pot.
Cover with water; cook over low heat for one hour.
Fry salt pork.
Add onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper.
Cook over low heat about five minutes. Remove from heat and add all remaining ingredients except parsley and vinegar.
Cook an additional hour over very low heat.
Add vinegar and parsley.
Let cook on stove for a few hours.
Taste and add additional seasoning, if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of flour with fruit and nuts, then mix together all ingredients and drop from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix. Spoon over cream cheese and spread on crackers.

title: pralines
directions: In a 2 quart sauce pan combine ingredients including pecans. Boil to soft ball stage 238° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir rapidly until gloss is lost.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoons.
Let harden.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Combine Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of chicken soup in a bowl.
Mix well.
Place chips in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover chips with pieces of chicken, pouring the mixture of tomatoes and soup over this.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Best when eaten hot.

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: In an oblong cooking pan, place chicken with cheese on top. Stir soup and milk.
Place over chicken. Combine butter and stuffing. Sprinkle over chicken. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: fudge cake a la mode
directions: Melt chocolate with 1/3 cup water according to package directions. Stir until smooth.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Meanwhile heat oven to 350°.	Grease 8 1/4 inch x 4 1/2 inch loaf pan; line bottom with waxed paper.
Put sugar, butter, salt, baking soda, and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Beat with mixer on high speed until well blended (mixture will not be creamy).	Add eggs one at a time, beating until creamy, pale, and fluffy.
Reduce mixer speed to medium and beat in 1/2 the flour, then 1/2 the milk.
Beat in remaining flour and milk, then chocolate until blended.
Scrape into prepared pan.	Bake 60 to 65 minutes until wooden pick comes out clean.	Cool cake in pan on a wire rack 5 minutes.
Run a knife around cake, invert onto wire rack; peel off paper and cool completely.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg and crushed pineapple with juice.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nutmeats.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar and milk.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the instant pudding and the can of crushed pineapple.
The pineapple mixture will be thick. Fold in the Cool Whip and marshmallows; mix very well.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 6 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well, but do not beat.
Pour into floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar and yeast together.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Fill muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400°.

title: cornbread stuffing casserole
directions: Crumble cornbread and mix with sage and pepper (be sure to taste).
Add enough broth to make a moist stuffing.
Layer half of stuffing in casserole dish.
Add chicken and then layer chopped eggs.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over all.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add syrup, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add nut meats, or spread on bottom of shell. Pour syrup mixture over nuts. Bake in a 350 degree oven until crust is browned to satisfaction.

title: cottage cheese and cold-cut platter
directions: In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese with green pepper, carrot and onion, mixing well.
Cut bologna slices in half.
Fold olive and pimento slices in half on the diagonal.
Cut cheese slices in half, diagonally.
To assemble, place cottage cheese mixture in center of large, round platter, mounding slightly in center.
Arrange bologna slices, overlapping around cottage cheese mixture.
Arrange olive and pimento slices around edge of platter; top with cheese slices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, sprinkle cottage cheese mixture with parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix and pour in graham cracker crust; top with Cool Whip.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayo, sugar and vanilla well. (Wash and dry grapes).
Add grapes and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Layer coconut and pecans in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Heat cream cheese, butter and sugar on low heat until a smooth mixture is produced.
Pour this mixture over cake mix. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients thoroughly.
Add zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add and mix well.
Blend in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix well and put in angel food cake pan.
Freeze.
Turn out on large plate.
Slice as needed.

title: sausage and red beans
directions: Cover beans in large pot and cook until almost done.
Add chili powder, salt, garlic powder, chopped onion and tomatoes or tomato sauce.
Let cook until tender.
Add cut up sausage and cook about 10 more minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and bell pepper.
Drain and add green chilies, salt, pepper and garlic to taste; set aside.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix together.
Marinate steaks overnight and grill.

title: greek spread for french bread
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on split French bread.
Bake at 400° until melted on top and slightly crusty around edges of bread.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Melt butter on a cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites until they are fluffy and form peaks.
Add sugar to whites.
Mix eggs and sugar with pecans.
Make sure all pecans are covered well.
Toast pecans in melted butter (stirring occasionally) until golden brown for 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove and place on wax paper until cool.

title: lime surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill in salad mold.
To serve, dip mold in warm water and release on cake plate.
Garnish as desired.

title: cherry bars
directions: Grease 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the remaining ingredients except pie filling and mix well.
Reserve one cup and set aside.
Spread remaining mixture in pan.
Carefully spread can of cherry pie filling over dough.
Use reserved dough to randomly drop over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Then add egg yolks, evaporated milk, water, vanilla and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour in already baked pie crust.
Cook pie crust according to directions before pouring pie filling in crust.

title: ezekiel's bread(ezekiel 4:9)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water; let sit for 10 minutes.
Mix the other ingredients.
Blend lentils, oil and small amounts of water in blender; place into large mixing bowl with remaining water.
Stir in 2 cups of mixed flour.
Place on floured bread board; knead until smooth.
Put in oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead again.
Cut dough and shape into loaves. Place in greased pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 4 loaves.

title: dirty rice(serves 40 people)
directions: Cook
ground beef, onions, peppers and other seasonings in a skillet
with
a
little
fat
until
done.
Add to this mixture, the
18 cups of already cooked rice.
Thoroughly mix. (Can be baked
for a few minutes on low temperature.
I do not bake my rice.
This is optional.)

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a tube cake pan.
In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar, nuts, butter and water.
Heat until butter melts.
Separate biscuits; cut each into quarters. Place in a large bowl. Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuits; toss lightly to coat evenly.
Spoon biscuits into tube pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 3 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Dip tomatoes into flour mixture and fry in hot fat until browned. Turn and brown on other side.

title: oatmeal breakfast bars
directions: Place margarine in a 2-quart glass measure.
Microwave on High (100% power) for 45 seconds or until margarine is melted.
Stir in sugar, blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon and baking powder; blend.
Stir in oats, then apple and raisins.
Pour mixture into a lightly sprayed 8 x 8-inch glass dish; level with spatula. Rotate midway through cooking.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until top is set but slightly moist.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
May be eaten warm or at room temperature.
Makes 16 bars.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except for apples.
Chill before serving for best flavor.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: baked devil's float
directions: Boil together 1 cup of sugar and 2 cups of water for 10 minutes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cream the shortening and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add alternately to the shortening mix with milk.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto the syrup already in dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp "touffee"
directions: Combine butter/margarine, Ro-Tel tomatoes, green pepper, green onions and celery.
Simmer for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Add shrimp and mushroom soup.
Simmer an additional 15 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: microwave cabbage rolls
directions: In microwave oval baking dish, mix spaghetti sauce and sugar. Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly; set aside.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: In crock-pot, melt cheeses.
Add meat and tomatoes.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips while dip is still warm. This can be frozen!

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: In small bowl, combine muffin mix and milk until blended.
Pour pie filling into round baking dish.
Put dollops of muffin mix on top, close together.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: ethel's black magic cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, dust top with powdered sugar or use your favorite frosting.

title: chili salad
directions: In large bowl, combine lettuce, corn chips, tomato, cheese, pepperoni and olives.

title: granny's salad dressing
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add vinegar and gelatin.
Mix with the last 4 ingredients; beat well.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: "thrashers" meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake in a large roasting pan at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
This is my grandmother's recipe.
We used it every year to feed the Thrash Machine Hands.

title: crumb cake
directions: Rub this
mixture
into a crumbly powder.
Take out 1/2 cup of this
mixture.
Now
add
to
the remainder 1 cup sour milk, 1 teaspoon
soda, and 1 egg.	Beat well.
After putting this cake in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup mixture on top.

title: prancer's salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip, then fold in remaining ingredients. Chill!

title: apple banana bread(a recipe from 1973 temple daily paper)
directions: Core and peel apples, chopped fine.
Sprinkle with a little lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Add mashed bananas to apples.
Mix well.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Stir in apples and bananas. Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt; sift together.
Stir into mixture and mix well.
Add flavoring and mix.
Pour into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans, 8 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool well.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla to the creamed mixture.
Fold berries with batter and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 15 muffins.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix vegetables and cheese. Pour dressing over vegetables, mix and stir well.
Cover.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally, every 1/2 hour.

title: 12-hour salad
directions: Place salad greens in bottom of a 3-quart bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with layers of celery, green peppers, onion and peas; do not toss.

title: nova scotia potato stuffing
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with butter. Add onions, salt, pepper, bread and summer savory.
Use to stuff turkey. Any remainder can be placed in a casserole and baked at 350° for 1 hour.
The summer savory is the secret ingredient that makes it special.

title: fiesta taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pot and drain excess grease. Stir in the refried beans until evenly blended. Add remaining ingredients and stir until heated through.

title: ice cream pudding
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip. Add pie filling and pineapple, mixing well with a spoon. Pour into glass casserole dish. Chill 1 hour. Big recipe.

title: egg rolls
directions: Shred all ingredients.
Season meat with soy sauce.
For filling, cook seasoned meat with oil in frying pan to bring up flavor.
Then add all ingredients together and stir briskly.
Drain exesss water, add peanut butter and mix evenly.
Put filling on egg roll skins.
Wrap fillings.
Fold both ends and roll skin to form egg roll.
Moisten edge of egg roll skin with cold water to seal the roll.
Deep fry in oil (350° to 400°).
Serve with sweet and sour sauce or soy sauce.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: In a large bowl mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice. Add very well drained pineapple, then add cherries and nuts which are both optional but add a great taste to this pie.
After combining all ingredients, then pour into pie shells and chill for at least 1 to 2 hours.
May be frozen for later use.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Very good and easy for a busy day.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Blend with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Grease Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture evenly into pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: penne salad with spring peas
directions: Combine pasta with peas, onion and pepper in salad bowl.
Mix vinegar, mayo, parsley, NutraSweet spoonful and peppercorns.
Pour dressing over salad; salt or pepper.
Makes 12 servings.
Contains 95 calories.

title: weight watchers slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, sweetener or sugar and salt and then cool.
Pour liquid over remaining ingredients and toss.
Freezes well.

title: ginger crispies
directions: Mix as for cookies. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll top and sides in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(Will crack on top.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil red potatoes; peel and cut into small chunks.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
In a frying pan, fry bacon, cut into small pieces and fry with chopped onion.
When onion and bacon are cooked, add salt, flour, sugar, vinegar and water and cook until sauce occurs.
Pour sauce over potatoes and serve hot.

title: eggplant in a jiffy
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine eggplant, celery, onion, parsley, oregano and butter.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce the heat, cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients, reduce the heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.

title: parelava
directions: Beat
together the egg white, castor sugar, vanilla and vinegar
for
minutes.
Add boiling water; beat for 12 minutes. Gently fold in the baking powder and corn flour; do not beat. Pile
on
a foiled, covered tray.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a very slow oven (250°).

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at
a
time,
beating well after each.
Sift flour and salt and add
alternately
with
milk.
Beat well and add red food coloring.
Bake
in large tube pan that has been buttered and floured
at
for
45	minutes to 1 hour.
Check with toothpick.	If it comes out clean, cake is done.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix cubed chicken with sour cream.
Butter deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make two layers as follows:
6 tortillas, 6 ounces salsa, 1/2 of chicken in sour cream mixture, 2 ounces chiles, 1 can olives and 1/2 pound cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: marinated cauliflower salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut in half.
Combine all ingredients in large skillet, in one layer.
Bring to a boil, stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: beef and cream spread
directions: Cut beef into small pieces with scissors.
Mix cheese and sour cream.
Add beef and pat into pie pan.
Cover with nuts.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 325° for 1 hour; cool and cut chicken into pieces.
Cook broccoli and arrange in a greased dish.
Add pieces of chicken.
In a separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; mix and pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese and melted butter over top.
Top with croutons. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lamb boysenberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; use on rack of lamb.
Put lamb in glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put fresh garlic, cracked pepper and fresh rosemary all over.
Pour sauce over and marinate 3 to 4 hours (not overnight).
Enough for 2 small racks.

title: peanut butter finger bars
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, egg and peanut butter. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cover immediately with chocolate chips. Let stand 5 minutes, then spread evenly.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; drain and mash (with margarine and a small amount of milk).
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole; top with butter or margarine and paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meringue mushrooms
directions: Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl at medium speed.
When fluffy, add cream of tartar and salt.
Increase speed to medium high and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until sugar is completely mixed.
Add vanilla and increase speed to high.
Beat until stiff.
Preheat oven to 225°.
Squeeze caps and stems with pastry bag.
Sprinkle caps with cocoa powder and bake for 1 hour at 225°.
Turn off oven and let meringue cool in oven about 1 hour, then remove from pan.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let chill, then form a ball.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pork chops.
Pour mixture over the pork chops.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes, or until pork chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Add rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate bits.
Dough is crumbly.
Roll into small balls (1-inch).
Bake on greased cookie sheets, about 15 minutes, at 350°.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: salsa verde green sauce(makes 1 quart)
directions: Add a little of 3 cups of chicken broth and strain.
Add to rest of broth and about 1/4 cup oil.
Heat.

title: peanut blossoms cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate Kisses, in large mixer bowl.
Mix on lowest speed until dough forms.
Shape into balls using rounded teaspoon of dough.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a chocolate Kiss. Press down firmly until cookie cracks around edges.

title: special potatoes
directions: Mix all this together and pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until dough is stiff and hard to stir.
Remove from heat and add scent (peppermint, extracts) if desired.
Knead immediately.
Store in airtight container. Keeps 4 to 6 weeks.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and soda; set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs; gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in desired amount of chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken(low-fat recipe)
directions: Spray chicken with butter flavored cooking spray (front and back). Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Drizzle each breast with 1/2 teaspoon honey. Bake an additional 2 to 3 minutes and serve.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Pour boiling water on raisins and let stand until ready for use.
Roll cracker crumbs into a fine dust.
Add spices.
Cut marshmallows into small pieces; whip the cream.
Add to pickle juice.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Be sure all cracker dust is absorbed.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and combine.
Add green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Add salt and pepper; toss.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cream.
Mix together and spread on crust and chill.

title: chill fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and put in a medium bowl.
Add Cool Whip and chopped pecans to the top of fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: glazed sweeties
directions: In skillet, combine syrup and margarine.
Simmer for two minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cook on low heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes, turning potato frequently to glaze.

title: fourth of july cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium saucepan heat 1/4 cup sugar and the butter.
Heat on low until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press mixture evenly over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: day before breakfast
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: easy stuffing for poultry or any side dish
directions: Break bread into small pieces and rinse quickly under hot water. Do not soak the bread.
Put into large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients and stir, mixing well.
Place into buttered pan that will hold all the ingredients.
Place foil over the dish and seal well at the edges. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Slowly add milk.
In separate bowl, whip the whipping cream until it forms peaks.
Fold together and put in an 8-inch graham cracker shell.
Keep in freezer.
Before serving, swirl on fudge and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: christmas baked ham
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pineapple juice, orange juice, vegetable oil, vinegar, dry mustard, cloves and ginger; mix well. Place ham in glass dish.
Pour mixture over ham, cover; refrigerate overnight.
Drain ham, reserving liquid.
Place ham in shallow baking pan.
Bake according to ham instructions, basting every 10 minutes with reserved liquid.
Before serving, garnish with parsley and cherries.

title: love food
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and vinegar to 300°, using a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour on greased pan to cool and then break apart and dip in melted chocolate and paraffin as before.

title: janet's easy mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwavable dish.
Microwave for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serve warm.

title: party scramble
directions: In small bowl, mix dill, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Set aside. Melt butter in large frying pan or stock pot.
Add cereal and stir until lightly brown.
Sprinkle with cheese mixture and gently stir.
Serve as party snack.
May be prepared ahead.
Keeps well. Serves 12.

title: cheese snaps
directions: Sift flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add water and mix well. Roll out and cut like dumplings.
Bake until done.

title: stuffed worcestershire beef logs
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt and 4 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce.
Divide in 6 parts.
Shape each part around each cheese strip.
Wrap a bacon strip around each log.
Brush with remaining Worcestershire sauce (leaving enough to baste once more). Bake at 475° for 15 to 18 minutes in oblong glass baking dish. Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add pepper, celery and onion; saute until vegetables are tender.
Add soup and tomatoes; mix well.
Pour this mixture over the rice in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple slices
directions: Place Dole slices in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serve warm, showered with coconut.
A beautiful dessert by itself.
Sensational with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6 people.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out and chop centers.
Mix chopped squash with everything, except bacon.
Fill shells; top with bacon.
Place on cookie sheet; cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12. (Can be made ahead and baked at the last minute.)

title: cucumber relish
directions: Do not peel cukes.
If seeds are large, take them out.
Leave the small ones in.
Put vegetables through a food chopper. Sprinkle a handful of canning salt over these and let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and add sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Cook pineapple, cornstarch and sugar until clear, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour in unbaked pie shell.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in hot oil.
Add ingredients.
Cover; simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove lid to allow mixture to dry out.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine
the first 3 ingredients.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cookies
directions: In a saucepan, melt 1 stick margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
If desired, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Blend buttermilk into pudding mix, using medium speed of mixer.
When smooth, blend in topping.
If consistency of mixture seems too thick, add a little more buttermilk.
Fold in fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges, reserving half a can of oranges for garnish.
Add colored marshmallows to mixture, if desired.
Swirl a design on top of salad with a tablespoon.
Gently arrange balance of mandarin orange slices in swirled design on top of salad.

title: fresh vegetable stew
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add squash, tomatoes and beans.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Add corn, salt and pepper. Cook for 3 minutes or until corn is tender.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw out potatoes before using!!!

Mix all ingredients together, except saving out 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 2 hours at 300° or 1 hour at 350°. One-half hour before done, sprinkle remaining cup of cheese over top.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in pan.
Let come to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
A small can of crushed pineapple added to this is also good.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and butter in saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potato, mixing gently.
Pour into buttered quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler, stir in raw sausage.
Mix well. Add Bisquick.
Remove from heat.
Roll into balls, about 1 inch thick.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields about 100 balls.

title: trio baked beans casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green pepper, remove seeds and scallop edges. Precook peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes and drain.
For crisp peppers, omit precooking.
Sprinkle inside of cups generously with salt.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichokes, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: brown bag burritos
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain. Add next 8 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Spoon 4 tablespoons of meat mixture on side of each tortilla. Top with 3 tablespoons cheese. Roll up. Wrap each one in paper towel, then in foil. Heat 1 minute in foil.

title: strawberry gooey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This will be a dry mix.

title: fried bread
directions: Mix and roll in strips, 3-inches long.
Slash in middle and fry.
(You can also take canned biscuits and roll out with rolling pan and fry.)

title: mock crab salad
directions: Cook rigatoni.
Thaw peas.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: eliza's hamburger macaroni
directions: Fry hamburger or ground chuck until light brown.
Drain and set aside.
In boiling water, place macaroni.
Cook according to package.
Drain.
Using the same cooker, add hamburger to macaroni mixture along with enough tomato juice to cover macaroni mixture completely.
Add sugar and stir well.
Let mixture simmer on warm until the macaroni takes on the flavor of the tomato juice.
Can add onions or green peppers if desired, but not necessary.
Serves 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix mashed bananas in; mix in all dry ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 15-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can; repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of tugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure that the rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup.
Open second quart if necessary.
Add 2 erge leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat again until high.
If druit gets stuck in the beaters, just pry it loos with a drewscriver.
Sample the rum again, checking for tonsisticity.
Next, sift 3 cups baking powder, a pinch of rum, a seaspoon of toda an a cup of pepper or salt (it really doesn't matter).
Sample the rum again.
Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 bablespoon of brown sugar, or whatever color you can find.
Wix mel.
Grease the oven and tun cake pan to 350 gredees.
Now pour the whole mess into the oven.
Maybe it would be better to forget the coven and the ake.
Just check the rum again and bo to ged.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8 to 1/4-inch and bake in pizza pan according to directions at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over baked cookie.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased
Bundt pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: jellied pigs feet
directions: Brown skin on pigs feet by holding over gas flame.
Wash and scrape well in warm water.
Place in kettle and add enough water to cover well over the meat.
Bring to boil and skim the foam. Lower heat and simmer slowly.
Add garlic, salt, whole peppercorns, onion and paprika.
Simmer until meat is tender and separate from bones, about 4 to 5 hours or 45 minutes in pressure cooker.

title: canned applesauce cake(makes a great gift)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Beat in eggs and applesauce. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda, salt and spices. Blend into applesauce mixture.
Add chopped nuts and raisins; mix well.
Fill clean greased or oiled wide mouth pint jars with prepared batter.
Bake open jars about 60 minutes in oven at 325°. When done, quickly remove one hot jar at a time and clean sealing edge.
Immediately apply and firmly tighten a two piece wide mouth canning lid.
The lid will form a vacuum seal as the jar cools. Jars of cooled cake may be stored with other canned foods or in freezer.
Cake is safe to eat as long as jars remain vacuum sealed.
Yields 8 wide mouth pint canning jars.

title: pickles in a hurry
directions: Wash cukes; leave on skin, then slice thin.
In a bowl, combine vegetables; sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Stir gently and allow to stand 1 hour.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar; pour over vegetables and stir to blend.
Cover and refrigerate.
Ready in 2 to 3 days.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook together first 4 ingredients.
Pour into large baking dish and add remaining ingredients.
Use 1 cup stuffing mix for topping. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Beat the butter with the sugar until creamy.
Add the eggs; beat 5 minutes more.
Add the flour, cinnamon and soda; beat 3 minutes more.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Place in a high 9-inch pan with a removable bottom, buttered and floured.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave seafood primavera(easy and elegant!)
directions: Cook fettucini as directed on package.
Drain, rinse and set aside.
Combine margarine, garlic and onion in 4-cup glass measure. Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until just about tender. Stir flour, bouillon, basil, nutmeg and pepper.
Blend in milk. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens slightly, stirring once.
Stir in seafood and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Layer pecans on bottom. Layer coconut over pecans. Mix cake according to directions. Pour over pecans and coconut. Melt cream cheese and butter together. Mix with powdered sugar. Pour on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cake will look like an earthquake has hit it.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: easy spinach souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 2-quart souffle dish; sprinkle bottom with cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add lemon juice and defrosted spinach.
Add salt and pepper.
Separate eggs; beat yolks into spinach sauce, one at a time, with a wire whisk.
Set mixture aside.

title: strawberry jam bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth. Add egg; mix well. Gradually add dry cake mix and corn flakes. Set aside 1 1/2 cups for topping. Press remaining dough into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Carefully spread jam over crust. Sprinkle with reserved dough; gently press down. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely on a wire rack. Cut into bars.

title: dan's london broil
directions: Clean London broil with clear water.
Coat meat with oil. Sprinkle both sides liberally with Accent, garlic powder and Lawry's. Cover with fresh crushed black pepper until every piece of meat is peppered.
Marinate for at least 1 hour (4 hours recommended).
Heat grill (hot as it will get.)
Sear first side until well charred; turn and sear 2nd side the same.
Cook until preferred doneness.
Let sit for 5 minutes before slicing sections.
Cut the meat and slice into 1/8 inch strips (cut across the grain).
Pour juice from cutting board over cut meat.
Serve as soon as possible.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Put fish in blender.
Add cream cheese, horseradish, pepper sauce, lemon juice, onion and parsley (saving 1/4 of parsley). Blend.
In separate bowl, combine potato chips with remaining chopped parsley.
Cover fish mixture with potato chip mixture. Completely chill before serving.
Serve with bread, crackers or raw vegetables.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Heat nectar; pour over jello.
Add frozen orange juice. Divide mixture in half.
Add sour cream to second half.
Let first half set, then pour on second half.
Refrigerate until completely set.
Cut into squares or spoon out.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Layer cheese in pie shell.
Layer onion, ham and broccoli. Mix milk and eggs.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: emergency corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients about 20 seconds.
Beat vigorously one minute.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread crushed graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixed pudding, chill. Layer bananas, Cool Whip, strawberries and pineapple.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: angel delight
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, tear half of cake into bite size pieces.
Pour half of pudding over cake.
Tear the remaining cake in pieces and pour remaining pudding over this.
Spread Cool Whip on top making a "well" in center.
Pour pie filling in "well" and over top.
Chill at least 2 hours.
You can try it with blueberry or strawberry pie filling.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cook until thick the egg, vinegar and sugar.
Add cheese, mango and cheese (you may want to double).

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, onions, red peppers, green peppers, salt and ice cubes.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Then squeeze and drain off all water.

title: rabbit with potato stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stuff the rabbit.
Sew up and place in a baking pan with strips of bacon over back of rabbit. Roast at 400° for 10 minutes.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over the rabbit and bake for about 1 hour.
Remove bacon and cook until brown.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles. Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles for the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan and saute the onions, garlic and celery for five minutes.
Add flour and blend well.
Over low heat, add cheese and milk, constantly stirring.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: anytime salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well and chill.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown onion, parsley and ground sirloin until lightly brown. Slice potatoes on top. Add catsup and water. Cook until potatoes are soft.
Add peas and cook for 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken or tuna vegetable salad
directions: Combine and let stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Just before serving, add 1 can shoestring potatoes.

title: jo's raspberry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange and walnuts.
Spoon into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Combine strawberries, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add enough water to make 3 gallons.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and combine all.
Put in freezer.
Serves approximately 100.

title: nine day cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine, also pepper and onion.
Place oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed in pan.
Stir until it boils and is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage mix.
Cover and let set until cool, then refrigerate.
The longer it sets, the better.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: miss sallie's candies yams
directions: Wash and peel yams.
Cut lengthwise in 1/4-inch thick slices. Place in baking pan.
Cover with 3/4 cup water and boil until tender, but not soft.
Sprinkle slices with sugar, salt and nutmeg. Dot with butter; bake until syrup forms, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and season meat to taste.
Mix Ro-Tel and soup together in separate bowl.
Line bottom of large bowl with 6 of the tortillas.
Layer 1/2 meat, beans, cheese and soup mixture.
Layer tortillas and repeat ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, or microwave on High 30 minutes (turning after first 15 minutes).

title: black walnut sheet cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Melt margarine and mix with cocoa and water.
Bring to rapid boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and eggs. Bake in cookie sheet pan with edge at 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring first five ingredients to boiling.
Simmer until tender. Add cheese and butter.
When cheese melts, add milk.
Thicken slightly.

title: louisiana hot chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, except chicken, and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: fettuccine
directions: Melt butter in separate pan.
Combine all other ingredients, except noodles, and add melted butter.
Cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: sonora chicken
directions: Crush Doritos; mix soups, chili, chicken, onion and picante sauce.
In a large casserole dish, layer Doritos, chicken mixture and cheese, then repeat.
Heat for approximately 8 minutes in microwave.
Serves 8 to 10 adults or 2 teenagers.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain and add rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasoning.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour (I do this part the night before).
When you're ready to cook, place chicken breasts on grill over medium -hot coals (or greased rack of broiler pan). Grill or broil for 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil.
Add flour all at once.
Stir until a ball forms. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven. Flatten crust and let cool.

title: fruit-ginger ale punch
directions: Note: All frozen juices require the 6 ounce cans.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut, core out and wedge cabbage thin.
Boil in salted water for 10 minutes.
Layer in casserole dish the cabbage, dressing, soup and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until tender at 350°.

title: mushrooms monterey
directions: In a heavy skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until lightly browned (about 2 minutes). Blend sour cream, flour, salt and pepper together and stir into mushrooms until just bubbly. Turn into shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley and bake in preheated 425° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: carbonara
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add the beaten eggs and toss.
Add bacon or salt pork which has been sauteed and browned.
Toss all together and add cheese.

title: jello confetti
directions: Dissolve each:
cherry, orange, lime and black-raspberry jello in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water for each (equals 6 cups water).

title: turkey hash(diabetic)
directions: To be served in the following order:

title: meatball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons steak sauce. Mix and shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oil in skillet. Drain fat from skillet.
Combine 1/3 cup steak sauce, brown sugar and butter with meatballs in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: cranberry-orange-walnut relish
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook cranberries, raisins, sugar, apple juice, ginger and orange peel for 5 minutes, stirring until cranberries pop and sugar is dissolved.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 15 minutes longer.

title: fruited cabbage salad
directions: In large bowl, layer the cabbage, bananas and tangerines. Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice. Place pineapple over the tangerines.

title: cheese and chili tortilla stack
directions: Place one tortilla on lightly greased rimmed baking pan and sprinkle evenly with 1/2 cup each Jack and Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon each of chilies and onions and 1 to 2 teaspoons olives.
Lightly sprinkle with Mexican seasoning or salsa.
Cover with tortilla and repeat layers until you have used 4 tortillas.
Top the pile with 1 more tortilla and brush it with melted butter/margarine.
Make second stack like first.
Bake uncovered in a 400° oven until browned, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut as desired.

title: light biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add mayonnaise and cut with flour cutter until flour looks coarse.
Then add water and lightly blend and shape into biscuits.
Makes 4 large or 6 small biscuits.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound chicken between 2 pieces of waxed paper to even thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and butter in skillet.
Cook chicken 4 minutes on each side. Do not overcook; remove to serving plate.

title: breakfast bran muffins(makes 10 dozen)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Keeps for up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.
Serve with cream cheese and fruit.

title: carrots and pineapple casserole
directions: Cook carrots which have been pared and sliced.
Drain pineapple chunks and reserve juice.
Heat juice; sweeten with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Thicken with cornstarch, using some reserved pineapple juice or orange juice.
Don't make too thick. Mix carrots, pineapple and sauce and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour undrained pineapple and cherry pie filling into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly over the fruit; do not mix.
Place slices of margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best served when warm.

title: chocolate chip-pudding cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add sugars and pudding mix, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla extract, mixing well.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to batter.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir together egg yolks, lemon peel and juice; set aside.
In a saucepan thoroughly mix sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually stir in boiling water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring briskly; continue to stir and let boil until clear and smoothly thickened, about 3 minutes.
Carefully stir in egg-lemon mixture and boil, stirring about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in butter.
Cool 5 minutes and pour into baked pastry shell.

title: english pecan toffee
directions: Combine in a saucepan the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Cook without stirring to 236° or until dropped in cold water and forms a soft ball.
Add the 2/3 cup pecans.
Continue cooking to 290° (soft crack) and mixture changes to a deep color. Stir in the soda.
Turn out on greased sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
Immediately spread with the chocolate chips or chocolate bars.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, eggs and lemon juice until thick; cool. Combine pineapple and Cool Whip.
Stir in apples and 1 1/2 cups of peanuts, then stir in the cooled mixture.
Top with remaining crushed peanuts.

title: fudge
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk and margarine. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.

title: overnight eggs
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage and ham quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Bake hash browns in pie plate for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and press into bottom of plate and up sides.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove.
Turn heat to 350°.
Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place sausage mixture in bottom of crust.
Pour milk and egg
mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine
ingredients.
Put mixture in ice cream freezer and put milk 1 1/2-inches from top.
Add 4 bananas mashed for variety or 1 1/2 cups of Hershey's chocolate syrup.

title: president reagan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and remove fat. Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Meanwhile, in separate dish beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients (except Mozzarella cheese). Set aside, then cook lasagna noodles until tender. In a 13x9x2 inch pan, arrange a layer of noodles, then 1/2 of cheese mixture, then a layer of Mozzarella cheese, then meat sauce. Repeat, making sure to end with meat sauce on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sunflower seed soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: brown sugar pork chops
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, put brown sugar, enough to cover bottom of pan.
Put sliced onion over brown sugar and browned pork chops over onion.
Put more brown sugar over chops and more onion slices.
Put tomato soup over.
Put 1 can of water around dish.
Cover dish.
Bake at 350° until tender (approximately 1 hour).

title: hot milk cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add flour mixture then add 1/2 c. hot milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater; pour into pan.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.
Good for brunch!

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Brown meat.
Halve zucchini.
Scoop out center, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Place in baking dish.
Chop zucchini center and mix with next 7 ingredients.
Spoon into shell and top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt together the butter and marshmallows. Add food coloring and stir. Pour in corn flakes. Stir and coat. Drop onto waxed paper. Add red hots on top.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add beans, sugar, salt, dill seed, pepper and dressing mix.
Mix well and heat through.
Add crumbled bacon.

title: asparagus lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as shown on package.
Drain and cut in half, crosswise.
In pan cook other ingredients, stirring until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
In buttered Pyrex dish layer 1/3 noodles, sauce, cheese and chicken.
Repeat layers twice. Bake in oven until cheese is well melted.

title: pacific paella
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch strips.
