Combine paprika, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Add chicken and stir until all seasonings are worked into chicken.
Cut sausage into 1/4 inch pieces; remove casing.
Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes.
Add enough water to chicken broth to make 3 3/4 cups.
Bring to a boil in a 12 inch skillet.
Stir in turmeric, saffron, rice, onion, garlic, chicken, sausage and tomatoes.
Reduce heat, cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in shrimp and green pepper; top with clams.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions.
Add chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti and set aside.
Cook chicken; take off bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Add all together.
Then, add mushroom soup, olives, spaghetti and toasted almonds.
Put in a large baking dish and let stand for 1 hour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Take out and sprinkle cheese over top and continue baking for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook celery and onion in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Then add the sauces.
I add garlic or any seasoning I so desire.
Simmer for at least an hour.
Arrange in dish:
cooked lasagna noodles, cooked sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add 2 cups sugar and mix until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Fold in cream, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Place the 4 teaspoons sugar, cinnamon and nuts in a bowl and stir.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and flour.
Heat milk.
Do not boil.
Add small amount of warm milk to sugar mixture, enough to make the mixture thin.
Then pour the mixture back into the heated milk.
Heat to a scald, stirring constantly, on medium heat for about 35 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature.
Add vanilla while cooling.
Freeze in 4-quart freezer.

title: pinwheels
directions: One package of crescent rolls equals two long rectangles. Pinch seams together.
Spread rectangles with cream cheese. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Roll rectangles (like cinnamon rolls).
Pinch seams.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill.

title: artichoke spread(serves 12)
directions: Drain artichokes and mash with fork.
Add mayonnaise and cheese. Place in greased baking dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix in double boiler over boiling water, the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir a little of the custard into the eggs, slowly, gradually adding a little more of the custard, until all has been combined.
Cook 5 minutes.
Chill overnight.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat for about 1 minute.
Add the onion, green pepper, beef and garlic.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, for 7 to 8 minutes or until onion is soft and beef is browned.
Add tomato sauce, cumin, cayenne pepper, chili powder, oregano and salt.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
If mix becomes too thick, add 2 to 3 tablespoons water, stirring occasionally.
Add beans.
Cover and simmer for 5 more minutes.

title: frog's eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.

title: special roast
directions: Combine roast, mushroom soup (rinse out each soup can with 4 ounces water) and add bouillon cubes.
Bake 2 to 3 hours until almost done.
Stir occasionally.
Add onions.
Cook 15 minutes. Add carrots and potatoes.
Continue cooking for 1 hour or until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: potato appetizer
directions: Wash potatoes.
Rub with small amount of oil.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Make hole in top of potato with a sharp knife.
Remove top and insides, leaving a lining of potato. Fill with sour cream, minced onion and salt.
An hour or ahead of serving, put tiny bit of caviar on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa for 20 minutes.*
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together in stove pot or large microwavable cup.
Bring to a boil.
Add kielbasa to stove pot and bring back to boil.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour together until thick.
Cool. Slice one layer of bananas on bottom of baked pie shell.
Sprinkle a layer of coconut.
Sprinkle a layer of pecans.
Then pour cooled pineapple over layers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: challah
directions: Sprinkle yeast and sugar into 1/4 cup very warm water and let stand for 5 minutes; then stir.
Mix flour and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center and drop in whole eggs, oil, 1 1/4 cups very warm water and the yeast mixture.
Work liquids into flour. Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Put into greased bowl and turn to grease top of dough.

Cover and let stand in warm place for one hour, punch down, cover and let rise 35 minutes or until doubled in bulk. Divide dough into three equal parts and between lightly floured hands roll dough into three ropes of even length.
Braid and put on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes or until light.
Brush with egg yolk and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Check after 15 minutes and if braid is very brown, cover with foil.

title: wendy's frosty
directions: Put ice cream in refrigerator to soften before using.
Put all ingredients in blender and mix.

title: christmas special fruitcake
directions: Combine nuts, dates and cherries.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to nut mixture; stir until well coated.
Beat eggs until foamy; add vanilla.
Add to nut mixture. Mix well.
Pour into greased and wax paper-lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs in small mixing bowl for 1 minute.
Add milk and then dry ingredients.
Beat until blended, scraping bowl.
Blend in shortening.
Bake in preheated waffle baker.
Makes 4 full size 4 section waffles or 8 smaller ones.

title: cheesy real casserole
directions: Place in casserole when cheese has melted.
Top with crushed corn flakes and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: senate bean soup(1872)
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Drain. Add the water, ham bone, pork, celery salt and onion. Cook beans until very soft. Remove bone and pork. Dice the meat.
Press the remaining bean mixture through coarse colander or cream thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Combine with meat, adding the mustard, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling, stirring. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate glaze frosting
directions: Melt shortening and first 3 ingredients until melted and smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 4 or 5 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, vanilla and quick oats.
Drop on waxed paper.
This is a quick cookie.
It tastes like fudge.
Peanut butter and oats make this a nutritious snack.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Add food coloring to small amounts for different colors.

title: ants on a tree(a chinese taco)
directions: Brown the ground turkey in a little oil.
Mince the fresh ginger.
Chop the scallions.
Mince the cloves of garlic until very fine.
Add the ginger, scallions and garlic to the browned meat.
Cook 20 minutes.
Stir in the soy sauce, sesame oil and hot sauce.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and ground pepper.
Serve in romaine lettuce leaves ala taco.

title: onion casserole
directions: Boil onions until tender, then drain. Grease bottom of 3-quart casserole with oleo and add 1 layer of onions, 1 layer of cream of mushroom soup and 1 layer of bread crumbs.
Repeat layers second time with a heavier layer of buttered crumbs for top layer. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until brown on top.

title: crab boil, quillian style
directions: Use enough water to cover one dozen crabs.
Add 1/2 can "flat" beer, 1 package crab boil and 1/4 pound salt.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Drop crabs in and boil for 20 minutes or until done.
Allow crabs to remain in water for 5 minutes after boiling.
(Adding 2 tablespoons vinegar to the water makes crabs easier to pick.)

title: bonnie blair's lemon chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pound to flatten slightly.
Saute in butter in skillet until lightly browned.
Remove, reserving pan drippings.
Stack chicken domino-style in baking dish.
Place a lemon slice between each piece.
Cut cheese into 4-inch strips. Place 1 piece between each chicken breast.
Cover top with remaining cheese.
Add wine to reserved pan drippings.
Cook over medium heat until slightly reduced.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add strawberries with juice, the drained pineapple and bananas.
Divide in half.
Pour half of mixture into Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream which has been mixed with cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Chill for 30 minutes, then pour other half of Jell-O mixture over all and chill well.

title: lima bean broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan twists
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough; separate into four rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Sprinkle both sides of each rectangle with cheese; cut into 6 lengthwise strips. Twist strips.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Cover while cooking.
Add wine, half and half, beaten egg yolks, salt and flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth, then add lobster.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to boil in medium saucepan, separating broccoli with fork.
Stir in cheese.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in roasting pan. Cook, covered, 4 to 4 1/2 hours at 325°.
Also good cooked in crock-pot.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Let sherbet soften a little.
Mix with ginger ale.
Drain cherries and add.
Low in calories and fat.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Can be eaten as a dip with tortilla chips or can be used as a salad or cold side dish.

title: homemade hershey's syrup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook 1 minute.
Remove; add vanilla.
Cool and store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Cook turkey and onion until brown.
Drain off any fat. Arrange noodles in baking dish.
Add meat mixture and remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

Healthy Choice cream of mushroom soup

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil zucchini until tender (about 6 minutes if cut in half).
Cool and scoop out pulp.
Lightly salt shells, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in heavy, 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil. Boil, without stirring, to soft ball stage.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Work in Crisco. Mix to a light dough with egg and milk. Press into greased shallow baking pan. Top with the apples by pressing down into the dough. Sprinkle with the sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares and serve hot with sweetened whipped cream.

title: cheese and bacon rolls
directions: Put cheese, cooked bacon and onion through food grinder (processor).
Stir in mustard, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise.
Form cheese mixture into 5 rolls about 1/2-inch in diameter x 6 1/2-inches long.
Cut each roll into 3 equal pieces. Place one piece of cheese mixture in center of each cooked crepe. Roll up crepes and cheese.
Just before serving, place in broiler pan.
Brush with butter and broil until bubbly.
Cut each crepe in 4 crosswise pieces.
Serve warm.

title: mound candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Heat to full boil.
Add coconut and set off.
Roll in balls.
Refrigerate.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Keep what is left and use later.

title: quick turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters of 3 or 4 halves 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Top each cluster with one caramel, slightly flattened.
Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until caramels soften. Remove to waxed paper.
Flatten caramels with spatula.
Top each candy with 1 milk chocolate bar while still warm.
Spread chocolate when melted.
Refrigerate a few minutes until chocolate hardens. Yields 4 dozen turtles.

title: italian beef
directions: Prepare in crock-pot.
Cook for 24 hours on low heat.
Cover roast with liquids.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and teaspoon of sugar.
Let set a few minutes.
Beat well together eggs, 1 1/4 cups sugar and shortening; add salt.
Add hot water and cold milk; mix well.
Add flour.
Mix, then turn out on floured board and knead.
Put in greased bowl. Let rise until triple in size.
Make in clover leaf rolls or pan rolls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 70 rolls.

title: mrs. dot's cheese ball
directions: Make sure cream cheese is room temperature. Mix all ingredients together. Shape into ball. Roll ball in chopped nuts if desired. Serve with wheat thins or ritz crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Put pudding mix and milk together; stir for 2 minutes.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Blend until creamy.
Use 1 pkg. crescent rolls for bottom crust on greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust. Top with 4 - 13 inch strips and 8 - 6 1/2 inch strips from 2nd package of crescent rolls.
Make a lattice top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20
minutes.
Cool and sprinkle
with slivered almonds and powdered sugar.

title: hershey kiss-peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add egg, vanilla, soda and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape into balls the shape of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar to coat.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes. Remove and press in Hershey Kiss.
Return to oven and bake for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes about 68 cookies.

title: melon and prosciutto
directions: Cut melon in half.
Scoop out seeds and fiber.
Cut each half lengthwise into 6 wedges and remove rind.
Cut crosswise slits 1 1/2 inches apart in each melon wedge.
Place several strips of Prosciutto over each wedge.
Push Prosciutto into slits using the blade of a table knife.
Makes 12 servings; 25 calories per serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken until tender; cool.
Remove from pan.
Cook broccoli; cool.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook and stir the first 4 ingredients over medium heat, stirring continuously until thick.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding.
Make
topping
of
egg whites and sugar.
Beat until fluffy and stiff.
Brown in oven under broiler.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel and finely chop peaches. If not very sweet, pour sugar over peaches and let set until sugar melts. Pour all the other ingredients into the ice cream bucket and stir with a wire whisk. Add the peaches. Finish filling to the fill line with homogenized milk. Freeze and enjoy.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil. Drain.
Transfer to slow cooker.
In separate bowl, whisk together mushroom soup and evaporated milk until smooth.
Pour over chops. Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours or low for 6 to 8 hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix sweetened water and Kool Aid. Add 1/2 gallon lime sherbet; mix well.
Chill. Add juice, ginger ale, and remaining sherbet just before serving.

title: southern smothered meat
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat and tenderize meat.
Dredge meat in flour.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil.
Remove to a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper. Saut onion slices in skillet drippings; add prepared Spanish Rice-A-Roni and sugar.
Pour rice mixture over meat.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 35 minutes, then uncovered for 20 minutes longer.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip, cherry pie filling and nuts.
Add a little red food coloring.

title: honey date bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl; let cool completely.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg to cooled mixture and then stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: heavenly dip
directions: Beat eggs, vinegar, sugar and salt together and cook until thickened.
Stir often.
Add cream cheese, beat until well blended and smooth.
Add green pepper and onion.

title: miss jessie's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and baste chicken frequently while cooking. Makes 1 quart.
Ample for 3 chickens.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line with wax paper; grease paper. Sprinkle prepared pan with coconut and pecans; set aside.

title: cheesy squash
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs, tasting for seasoning.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts. Pour into crust. Makes 2 pies.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: wilma berry's crab dip
directions: In double boiler, melt butter. Saute onion and bell pepper. Add flour. Combine Pet milk with same amount of water. Add this to mixture to make cream sauce. To this add pimento, crab meat, nutmeg, cayenne pepper, salt and Lea & Perrins. Add Cheddar cheese. Heat in top of double boiler, stirring until mixture thickens. If it gets too thick for a dip, a little half and half can be added. Place in chafing dish to serve with Melba toast. Can be prepared in advance and reheated in chafing dish.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Add dry cake mix and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 370° for 40 minutes.

title: linda's chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain.
Put together in pot. Bring to boil.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Good with cheese on top.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and garlic.
Simmer for 15 minutes, uncovered; stir frequently.
Cut cabbage into 6 wedges.
Cook in a small amount of salted, boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a large casserole dish.
Spread 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1 stick melted margarine over top of mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: roast-potato wedges
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut each baking potato into 8 wedges.
Place potato wedges, cut side down, on the rack of a broiler pan.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika to taste.
Broil 3 inches from heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Turn to expose the other cut side and brush with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Continue to broil until tender, about 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 3 inch loaf pan. In a large bowl combine first 7 ingredients. Form into a loaf. Place into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and pour off juice. Bake about 10 minutes longer. Prepare sauce by mixing the final 4 ingredients. Place meat loaf on a platter and cover with sauce.

title: diabetic cinnamon bread pudding(this is a diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat milk and margarine to simmering in a medium saucepan. Remove from heat and stir until margarine is melted. Cool 10 minutes. Beat eggs and egg whites in a large bowl until foamy; mix in Equal, spices and salt. Mix milk mixture into egg mixture. Mix in the bread cubes. Spoon the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Place casserole in a roasting pan on oven rack. Add 1-inch of hot water. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven until pudding is set and a sharp knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, salad oil, onion, salt and pepper until brown and crumbly.
Add
tomato soup, water, tomato sauce and raw rice and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Pour over chopped cabbage in a 2 qt dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: gingerbread with citrus fluff
directions: Cream until light 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup boiling water, beating after each addition.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with Citrus Fluff.

title: christine's nifty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the inside of 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over low heat until melted.
In mixing bowl, stir the cocoa and sugar together, then stir in melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla and stir.
Add the flour and salt; mix until smooth and add walnuts.
Pour mixture into pan and spread evenly.
Bake until brownies just begin to pull away from sides or until a toothpick comes out clean, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: fudge mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Chil until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Melt butter.
Stir in 1 tablespoon reserved syrup.
Place about 1/2 tablespoon butter mixture in each of eight 6-ounce custard cups.
Add 1 tablespoon brown sugar to each.
Arrange pineapple on top sugar.
Place cherry half in center.
Prepare cake mix following package directions and using remaining pineapple syrup plus enough water to equal liquid called for on package.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each cup. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; invert onto plate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream together.
Break cake in pieces and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover cake with pudding mix.
Put a layer of pie filling on top.
Layer with strawberries, then blueberries.
Repeat the process.
Layer of cake and top with whipped cream.
Put strawberries on top.

title: baked asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together cheese, butter and crumbs.
In a separate bowl, blend soup and juice from asparagus.
Layer in buttered casserole dish the crumb mixture, asparagus, soup and nuts.
End layering with crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: breakfast egg pizza
directions: Spread out rolls on 13 x 9-inch pan and lap up on edges. Cover bottom with grated cheese.
Put sausage on top of cheese. Blend milk, eggs and spices in blender and pour over sausage and cheese.
Cook for 20 minutes at 425°.
Slice and serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cookie salad
directions: Other fruit may be added.
Simple and very good.

title: monkey bread
directions: Next, melt these ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake a 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then flip over onto serving tray.

title: south sea baked chicken
directions: Mix ingredients with chicken stock (can be made from bouillon cubes) and stuff fryers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut auf bayrische art(bavarian style sauerkraut)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with warm water, drain well.
Cook onion and bacon in butter until onion is soft.
Add the drained kraut, caraway seed and sugar.
Cover tightly.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add bouillon and wine.
Simmer 1/2 hour longer or until kraut is cooked to your taste.

Serve as a vegetable with sauerbraten or Kolbshaxe, or top with a selection of pork products such as boiled thick slabs of bacon, pig's feet, bratwurst, frankfurters, blood sausage or Regensburg sausage.
On such a plate, Erbsenpuree and mashed potatoes are always served.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Prebake crust as directed on package.
Melt butter; add Karo syrup, sugar and eggs; blend.
Combine chocolate chips and pecans; sprinkle evenly in bottom of crust.
Pour blended ingredients over chips/nuts and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then debone.
Boil onion and celery in broth until tender.
Add spaghetti and bouillon cubes.
Cook until tender.
Add mushroom and celery soups, deboned chicken and chili powder.
Simmer to desired thickness.
Enjoy.

title: suet pudding
directions: Put in can and steam for 3 hours.
Three recipes make 3 Spry cans and 1 coffee can.

title: potatoes and cube steaks
directions: Put steaks on bottom of baking dish.
Mix potatoes, soup, chopped onion, salt and pepper and a half can of water together. Spread over steaks.
Bake for 1 hour covered with foil and 1/2 hour uncovered.
Bake at 375°.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Add cheese.
Brown meat, drain and add onion.
Cook until done.
Stir in tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
In baking dish, layer noodles, sauce and cheese; repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Combine the flour, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic salt in bag.
Shake chicken pieces in flour mixture until well coated. Melt margarine in shallow casserole.
Lay chicken, skin side down, into casserole and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes until golden brown on all sides.

title: chicken spaghetti(our family favorite!)
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in iron skillet until onion is clear.
Add chicken broth to mixture; simmer.
In a small bowl, combine Ro-Tel, Cheddar cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine soup mixture, chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute rice in hot oil in a large skillet 3 to 5 minutes. Combine rice, tomatoes and next 5 ingredients.
Add water; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour Cheddar cheese soup over rice.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Put cabbage, carrots, onions and peppers through food chopper.
Add salt; let stand 2 hours.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Put in jars cold and cover with paraffin.

title: basic salt dough
directions: Combine flour and salt; add water a little at a time.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until smooth, putty like.
Lightly oil cookie sheet. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick, cut out as desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until rock hard.
Paint as you wish.
Spray completely with polyurethane to prolong life of the ornament.

title: 1 loaf bread recipe
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water. In a bowl, take warm milk and add lard and sugar until lard is melted, then add the first 1 1/2 cups flour; stir, then add salt and the remaining flour. Make dough into ball and let rise once. Punch/knead the bread. Shape into loaf and put in bread pan. Let rise again and then bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Lightly grease the pan.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain on paper towel and crumble.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean, approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together. Separate egg yolks.
Add milk to beaten yolks.
In a black skillet or pan, melt the margarine. Add the dry ingredients. Add the milk and egg yolk mixture. Stir continuously until it thickens.
Remove from heat. Add flavoring and pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar, 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread on pie and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meatballs in beer
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan; simmer 20 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients; form into small meatballs.
Brown in oven; drain fat.
Add meatballs to beer sauce; simmer 10 minutes (I add 1/2 cup or more brown sugar to beer sauce, depending how sweet you want it).

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix dates, nuts and soda.
Add boiling water; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour.
Excellent!

title: butter pecan frosting
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Beat in enough sweet milk to get spreading consistency.
Add pecans.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt; cream it.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in paper baking cups and place in muffin pan.
Freeze.
Garnish with cherry on stem before serving.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil in cooker for
minute sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and milk.
Add peanut
butter,
oats, coconut and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop mixture
onto
wax
paper by tablespoon.
Dip bottom of glass into cold water and flatten cookies.
Let stand about 1/2 hour and serve.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken dijon
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave 8 to 10 minutes, until tender. While they are cooking, in a large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add barbecue sauce and tarragon; toss until heated through.

title: coquille st. jacques in cheese sauce
directions: Simmer scallops in wine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain, reserve liquid; rinse scallops in cold water.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt; cook, stirring 1 minute. Gradually whisk in reserved liquid; whisk over heat until smooth. Remove from heat; stir in cheese until melted.
Stir scallops into sauce.
In shallow glass ovenproof bowls or dishes with raised lips, spread mashed potatoes over bottoms and up sides to form a cup.
Fill with scallop mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° until sauce bubbles, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake(easy and quick)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Add flour (some at a time) and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan until firm, about 30 minutes.
Turn out, leaving pan over released cake an additional 30 minutes.
This keeps cake from getting crusty.
Use plain or with a sugar glaze on top.
It's already excellent, but the glaze really makes it yummy.

title: one pan dinner
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Bake longer if juicy.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put in a saucepan and bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients. Sift together flour and sugar.
Pour first mixture over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add to eggs the buttermilk or sour milk, soda and vanilla.
Add batter and pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while still hot.

title: stars (spitzbuben)
directions: Mix margarine, almonds, sugar, flour and vanilla together. Roll out thin, using star cookie cutter to cut them out.
Bake at 350° until light brown only.
Cool, then place a little jam on one side of star and put second star on top, like a sandwich.
Then roll the sandwich star cookie in granulated sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar, Crisco and cool.
Add potatoes, flour and egg whites.
Mix thoroughly and knead until well blended.
Put in covered bowl, lightly greased for several hours or overnight. Roll and cut like biscuits.
Dip in hot Crisco and fold over.
Let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients
into
a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening,
eggs
and molasses.
Mix together, then gradually add hot water and mix well.
Bake in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake
minutes
Ice in same pan with Minute Caramel Icing.

title: country apple cranberry sauce
directions: In medium pan, combine washed cranberries, sugar, water and apple. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in orange peel. Cool completely and serve or refrigerate. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients; use enough dill pickle juice to make a sauce consistency.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Set aside about 1/2 cup mixture and with spoon, press remainder into 9-inch pie pan to form a shell.
In saucepan, mix 1 cup milk, corn, salt, pepper and onion.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Blend flour and remaining milk; stir into hot mixture and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Gradually add eggs, stirring vigorously.
Pour into lined pie pan and sprinkle with reserved crumbs and paprika.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes. Cut in wedges and serve piping hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix in pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar; add Cool Whip and spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Refrigerate 40 minutes.
Combine strawberry gelatin and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and pour over cream cheese layer. Chill until set.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions.
Drain grease and put in a casserole dish.
Add peas.
Mix can of cream of mushroom soup with 1/3 cup of water and add to casserole dish.
Stir ingredients.
Put cheese on top; then cover with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until Tater Tots brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in pan. Cover and bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Stir.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 cups.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 13 x 9-inch ungreased baking dish, place 1/4-inch frozen slices of cookie dough (pat into a solid layer to cover bottom of pan).
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Spoon over cookie dough in pan.
Pat another layer of 1/4-inch slices of dough onto cream cheese mixture.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool completely and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Cut into squares.
Sift powdered sugar over tops.

title: hot sauce dip
directions: Blend together in blender 3 seconds.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Let set a couple of hours before eating.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In double boiler melt butter and peanut butter together.
Add vanilla flavoring and confectioners sugar.
If needed, add milk. Stir until creamy.
Add nuts. Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix milk, apple juice, egg whites and oil in bowl or blender.
Add dry ingredients to mix.
Add chopped apple.
Line the muffin pans with baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake in 425° oven for 17 minutes.
After cooling, store in a large plastic bag to retain moisture and softness.
Freezes well for use later.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Butter 9 x 13 glass pan and place potatoes in bottom of pan. Drizzle butter on top. Mix cheeses and put on top of potatoes. Reserve some cheddar for the top.
Pour whipping cream over top. Place remainder of cheddar cheese over top and sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° till bubbly and slightly brown.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in Crisco, using a pastry blender, until in form of pea size chunks.
Divide dough in two parts.
Roll out and place in pie plate.

title: blondie brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine shortening and milk in large saucepan.
Place on low heat until shortening melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add egg.
Stir until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan. Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: baked chicken parmesan(serves 6)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
In a shallow bowl, combine the butter with the mustard.
In another shallow bowl, blend together the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and basil.
Dip the chicken pieces first into the mustard mixture and then coat with the bread crumb mixture.
Place, skin side up, in the baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise. Fold in whipped cream and chopped nuts. Use over fruit salads.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil potatoes and beets.
Boil chicken breast, cut into small pieces.
Put mayonnaise onto chicken and mix all ingredients together.
Add more mayonnaise, if necessary.
Serve cold.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a very sharp knife cut beef across grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick.

title: crunchy peanut butter bars
directions: Heat peanut butter and oleo until smooth.
Take off heat.
Add Rice Krispies and sugar.
Mix.
Form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. In double boiler, heat bar, chips and paraffin until smooth.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots lengthwise and cook 18 to 20 minutes in salt water.
Add brown sugar, salt and orange peel in skillet.
Cook 12 minutes until bubbly.
Add cooked carrots; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until carrots are glazed and heated through, about 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: juju's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Combine sifted flour, salt and baking soda.
Add creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough about 3 inches apart onto ungreased nonstick baking sheet.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars until creamy; add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt together. Add vanilla to butter mixture, then add flour.
Make into a ball the size of a marble.
Roll in granulated sugar and put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with the bottom of sugared glass.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Beat egg and combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until pudding thickens.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: patty's easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Set meat mixture aside.
Heat enchilada sauce and cream of chicken soup.
Do not let mixture boil.

title: creole lima beans
directions: Heat tomatoes to
boiling
in
quart saucepan.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, separating beans with fork; reduce heat.	Cover
and
simmer until beans are tender, about 5 minutes.
Makes 5 servings, 75 calories per serving.

title: potatoes la la
directions: Scrub potatoes well; grease with shortening.
Put into 400° oven and bake for 1 hour or until fork-tender.
Split potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out into large bowl of electric mixer. Add all other ingredients except egg and beat until blended.
Add egg and continue to beat until smooth and creamy.
Fill 6 potato shell halves (discard remaining shells); sprinkle top of each potato half with additional grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.

title: crazy biscuits
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 biscuits.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Stir lemonade and strawberry mixes and water until well blended.
Add ginger ale, sliced strawberries and ice cubes. Serves 16 cups.

title: swiss steak
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, mustard and pepper.
Sprinkle half of flour mixture over one side of steak; cover with plastic wrap and pound with flat side of meat mallet.
Repeat on other side with remaining flour mixture.
Discard plastic wrap.

title: amaretto liqueur
directions: Boil water, sugar and Karo for 50 minutes.
Take off heat and add coffee.
Cool to room temperature and add grain alcohol, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Pour into smaller bottles when cool.

title: buttermilk lemon cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan.
Mix well. Add buttermilk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine.

title: tuna crescent roll
directions: Stir together tuna, mayonnaise, onion and pimento.
Unroll dinner roll dough.
Do not separate into triangles.
Pinch edges together to form one large rectangle of dough.
Spread with tuna mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll, starting with longest side. Place seam side down on greased baking sheet, curving edges to form crescent shape.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Prepare chicken gravy mix as directed on envelope; stir in dill weed.
Slice crescent and serve with gravy.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Fold marshmallows, fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and orange sections into mixture.
Then add the unwhipped whipping cream and nuts or coconut (optional).

title: emily's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and let cool.
Mix olives, red onion, bell peppers and tomatoes together.
Add spaghetti and mix well.

title: oriental meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass baking dish.
Place meat into mixture and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, turning several times. Prepare meat as desired.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Fill cupcake tins 2/3 full. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven when cupcakes sink in middle (about 5 minutes).

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Put on stove milk, let get hot, not boiling.
Add butter and let melt.
Beat eggs well until lemon color and thick; adding sugar, gradually mix well.
Add flour and baking powder, vanilla and mix well.
Add milk to mixture and stir well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add egg whites to creamed mixture and beat at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Stir together flours, spices, baking powder, baking soda and salt until well blended.
Add to creamed mixture along with applesauce, sweetener and nuts.
Mix at medium speed only until the flour is moistened (do not overbeat).
Spread evenly in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan that has been greased with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean from the center and the bread pulls away from sides of the pan.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and turn out onto a wire rack to cool to room temperature.
